334 explicit BlockEffectControlMap(Zone* temp_zone) : map_(temp_zone) {}
335
336 BlockEffectControlData& For(BasicBlock* from, BasicBlock* to) {
337 return map_[std::make_pair(from->id().ToInt(), to->id().ToInt())];
338 }
339
340 const BlockEffectControlData& For(BasicBlock* from, BasicBlock* to) const {
341 return map_.at(std::make_pair(from->id().ToInt(), to->id().ToInt()));
342 }
343
344 private:
345 using Key = std::pair<int32_t, int32_t>;
346 using Map = ZoneMap<Key, BlockEffectControlData>;
347
348 Map map_;
349};

351// Effect phis that need to be updated after the first pass.
352struct PendingEffectPhi {
353 Node* effect_phi;
354 BasicBlock* block;
355
356 PendingEffectPhi(Node* effect_phi, BasicBlock* block)
357 : effect_phi(effect_phi), block(block) {}
358};

360void UpdateEffectPhi(Node* node, BasicBlock* block,
361 BlockEffectControlMap* block_effects) {
362 // Update all inputs to an effect phi with the effects from the given
363 // block->effect map.
364 DCHECK_EQ(IrOpcode::kEffectPhi, node->opcode())((void) 0);
365 DCHECK_EQ(static_cast<size_t>(node->op()->EffectInputCount()),((void) 0)
366 block->PredecessorCount())((void) 0);
367 for (int i = 0; i < node->op()->EffectInputCount(); i++) {
368 Node* input = node->InputAt(i);
369 BasicBlock* predecessor = block->PredecessorAt(static_cast<size_t>(i));
370 const BlockEffectControlData& block_effect =
371 block_effects->For(predecessor, block);
372 Node* effect = block_effect.current_effect;
373 if (input != effect) {
374 node->ReplaceInput(i, effect);
375 }
376 }
377}
378
379void UpdateBlockControl(BasicBlock* block,
380 BlockEffectControlMap* block_effects) {
381 Node* control = block->NodeAt(0);
382 DCHECK(NodeProperties::IsControl(control))((void) 0);
383
384 // Do not rewire the end node.
385 if (control->opcode() == IrOpcode::kEnd) return;
386
387 // Update all inputs to the given control node with the correct control.
388 DCHECK(control->opcode() == IrOpcode::kMerge ||((void) 0)
389 static_cast<size_t>(control->op()->ControlInputCount()) ==((void) 0)
390 block->PredecessorCount())((void) 0);
391 if (static_cast<size_t>(control->op()->ControlInputCount()) !=
392 block->PredecessorCount()) {
393 return; // We already re-wired the control inputs of this node.
394 }
395 for (int i = 0; i < control->op()->ControlInputCount(); i++) {
396 Node* input = NodeProperties::GetControlInput(control, i);
397 BasicBlock* predecessor = block->PredecessorAt(static_cast<size_t>(i));
398 const BlockEffectControlData& block_effect =
399 block_effects->For(predecessor, block);
400 if (input != block_effect.current_control) {
401 NodeProperties::ReplaceControlInput(control, block_effect.current_control,
402 i);
403 }
404 }
405}
406
407void RemoveRenameNode(Node* node) {
408 DCHECK(IrOpcode::kFinishRegion == node->opcode() ||((void) 0)
409 IrOpcode::kBeginRegion == node->opcode() ||((void) 0)
410 IrOpcode::kTypeGuard == node->opcode())((void) 0);
411 // Update the value/context uses to the value input of the finish node and
412 // the effect uses to the effect input.
413 for (Edge edge : node->use_edges()) {
414 DCHECK(!edge.from()->IsDead())((void) 0);
415 if (NodeProperties::IsEffectEdge(edge)) {
416 edge.UpdateTo(NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node));
417 } else {
418 DCHECK(!NodeProperties::IsControlEdge(edge))((void) 0);
419 DCHECK(!NodeProperties::IsFrameStateEdge(edge))((void) 0);
420 edge.UpdateTo(node->InputAt(0));
421 }
422 }
423 node->Kill();
424}

426void TryCloneBranch(Node* node, BasicBlock* block, Zone* temp_zone,
427 Graph* graph, CommonOperatorBuilder* common,
428 BlockEffectControlMap* block_effects,
429 SourcePositionTable* source_positions,
430 NodeOriginTable* node_origins) {
431 DCHECK_EQ(IrOpcode::kBranch, node->opcode())((void) 0);
432
433 // This optimization is a special case of (super)block cloning. It takes an
434 // input graph as shown below and clones the Branch node for every predecessor
435 // to the Merge, essentially removing the Merge completely. This avoids
436 // materializing the bit for the Phi and may offer potential for further
437 // branch folding optimizations (i.e. because one or more inputs to the Phi is
438 // a constant). Note that there may be more Phi nodes hanging off the Merge,
439 // but we can only a certain subset of them currently (actually only Phi and
440 // EffectPhi nodes whose uses have either the IfTrue or IfFalse as control
441 // input).
442
443 // Control1 ... ControlN
444 // ^ ^
445 // | | Cond1 ... CondN
446 // +----+ +----+ ^ ^
447 // | | | |
448 // | | +----+ |
449 // Merge<--+ | +------------+
450 // ^ \|/
451 // | Phi
452 // | |
453 // Branch----+
454 // ^
455 // |
456 // +-----+-----+
457 // | |
458 // IfTrue IfFalse
459 // ^ ^
460 // | |
461
462 // The resulting graph (modulo the Phi and EffectPhi nodes) looks like this:
463
464 // Control1 Cond1 ... ControlN CondN
465 // ^ ^ ^ ^
466 // \ / \ /
467 // Branch ... Branch
468 // ^ ^
469 // | |
470 // +---+---+ +---+----+
471 // | | | |
472 // IfTrue IfFalse ... IfTrue IfFalse
473 // ^ ^ ^ ^
474 // | | | |
475 // +--+ +-------------+ |
476 // | | +--------------+ +--+
477 // | | | |
478 // Merge Merge
479 // ^ ^
480 // | |
481
482 SourcePositionTable::Scope scope(source_positions,
483 source_positions->GetSourcePosition(node));
484 NodeOriginTable::Scope origin_scope(node_origins, "clone branch", node);
485 Node* branch = node;
486 Node* cond = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(branch, 0);
487 if (!cond->OwnedBy(branch) || cond->opcode() != IrOpcode::kPhi) return;
488 Node* merge = NodeProperties::GetControlInput(branch);
489 if (merge->opcode() != IrOpcode::kMerge ||
490 NodeProperties::GetControlInput(cond) != merge) {
491 return;
492 }
493 // Grab the IfTrue/IfFalse projections of the Branch.
494 BranchMatcher matcher(branch);
495 // Check/collect other Phi/EffectPhi nodes hanging off the Merge.
496 NodeVector phis(temp_zone);
497 for (Node* const use : merge->uses()) {
498 if (use == branch || use == cond) continue;
499 // We cannot currently deal with non-Phi/EffectPhi nodes hanging off the
500 // Merge. Ideally, we would just clone the nodes (and everything that
501 // depends on it to some distant join point), but that requires knowledge
502 // about dominance/post-dominance.
503 if (!NodeProperties::IsPhi(use)) return;
504 for (Edge edge : use->use_edges()) {
505 // Right now we can only handle Phi/EffectPhi nodes whose uses are
506 // directly control-dependend on either the IfTrue or the IfFalse
507 // successor, because we know exactly how to update those uses.
508 if (edge.from()->op()->ControlInputCount() != 1) return;
509 Node* control = NodeProperties::GetControlInput(edge.from());
510 if (NodeProperties::IsPhi(edge.from())) {
511 control = NodeProperties::GetControlInput(control, edge.index());
512 }
513 if (control != matcher.IfTrue() && control != matcher.IfFalse()) return;
514 }
515 phis.push_back(use);
516 }
517 BranchHint const hint = BranchHintOf(branch->op());
518 int const input_count = merge->op()->ControlInputCount();
519 DCHECK_LE(1, input_count)((void) 0);
520 Node** const inputs = graph->zone()->NewArray<Node*>(2 * input_count);
521 Node** const merge_true_inputs = &inputs[0];
522 Node** const merge_false_inputs = &inputs[input_count];
523 for (int index = 0; index < input_count; ++index) {
524 Node* cond1 = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(cond, index);
525 Node* control1 = NodeProperties::GetControlInput(merge, index);
526 Node* branch1 = graph->NewNode(common->Branch(hint), cond1, control1);
527 merge_true_inputs[index] = graph->NewNode(common->IfTrue(), branch1);
528 merge_false_inputs[index] = graph->NewNode(common->IfFalse(), branch1);
529 }
530 Node* const merge_true = matcher.IfTrue();
531 Node* const merge_false = matcher.IfFalse();
532 merge_true->TrimInputCount(0);
533 merge_false->TrimInputCount(0);
534 for (int i = 0; i < input_count; ++i) {
535 merge_true->AppendInput(graph->zone(), merge_true_inputs[i]);
536 merge_false->AppendInput(graph->zone(), merge_false_inputs[i]);
537 }
538 DCHECK_EQ(2u, block->SuccessorCount())((void) 0);
539 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(matcher.IfTrue(), common->Merge(input_count));
540 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(matcher.IfFalse(), common->Merge(input_count));
541 int const true_index =
542 block->SuccessorAt(0)->NodeAt(0) == matcher.IfTrue() ? 0 : 1;
543 BlockEffectControlData* true_block_data =
544 &block_effects->For(block, block->SuccessorAt(true_index));
545 BlockEffectControlData* false_block_data =
546 &block_effects->For(block, block->SuccessorAt(true_index ^ 1));
547 for (Node* const phi : phis) {
548 for (int index = 0; index < input_count; ++index) {
549 inputs[index] = phi->InputAt(index);
550 }
551 inputs[input_count] = merge_true;
552 Node* phi_true = graph->NewNode(phi->op(), input_count + 1, inputs);
553 inputs[input_count] = merge_false;
554 Node* phi_false = graph->NewNode(phi->op(), input_count + 1, inputs);
555 if (phi->UseCount() == 0) {
556 DCHECK_EQ(phi->opcode(), IrOpcode::kEffectPhi)((void) 0);
557 } else {
558 for (Edge edge : phi->use_edges()) {
559 Node* control = NodeProperties::GetControlInput(edge.from());
560 if (NodeProperties::IsPhi(edge.from())) {
561 control = NodeProperties::GetControlInput(control, edge.index());
562 }
563 DCHECK(control == matcher.IfTrue() || control == matcher.IfFalse())((void) 0);
564 edge.UpdateTo((control == matcher.IfTrue()) ? phi_true : phi_false);
565 }
566 }
567 if (phi->opcode() == IrOpcode::kEffectPhi) {
568 true_block_data->current_effect = phi_true;
569 false_block_data->current_effect = phi_false;
570 }
571 phi->Kill();
572 }
573 // Fix up IfTrue and IfFalse and kill all dead nodes.
574 if (branch == block->control_input()) {
575 true_block_data->current_control = merge_true;
576 false_block_data->current_control = merge_false;
577 }
578 branch->Kill();
579 cond->Kill();
580 merge->Kill();
581}

790void EffectControlLinearizer::UpdateEffectControlForNode(Node* node) {
791 // If the node takes an effect, replace with the current one.
792 if (node->op()->EffectInputCount() > 0) {
793 DCHECK_EQ(1, node->op()->EffectInputCount())((void) 0);
794 NodeProperties::ReplaceEffectInput(node, gasm()->effect());
795 } else {
796 // New effect chain is only started with a Start or ValueEffect node.
797 DCHECK(node->op()->EffectOutputCount() == 0 ||((void) 0)
798 node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kStart)((void) 0);
799 }
800
801 // Rewire control inputs.
802 for (int i = 0; i < node->op()->ControlInputCount(); i++) {
803 NodeProperties::ReplaceControlInput(node, gasm()->control(), i);
804 }
805}

807void EffectControlLinearizer::ProcessNode(Node* node, Node** frame_state) {
808 SourcePositionTable::Scope scope(source_positions_,
809 source_positions_->GetSourcePosition(node));
810 NodeOriginTable::Scope origin_scope(node_origins_, "process node", node);
22
←
Calling constructor for 'Scope'
→
811
812 // If basic block is unreachable after this point, update the node's effect
813 // and control inputs to mark it as dead, but don't process further.
814 if (gasm()->effect() == jsgraph()->Dead()) {
815 UpdateEffectControlForNode(node);
816 return;
817 }
818
819 // If the node needs to be wired into the effect/control chain, do this
820 // here. Pass current frame state for lowering to eager deoptimization.
821 if (TryWireInStateEffect(node, *frame_state)) {
822 return;
823 }
824
825 // If the node has a visible effect, then there must be a checkpoint in the
826 // effect chain before we are allowed to place another eager deoptimization
827 // point. We zap the frame state to ensure this invariant is maintained.
828 if (region_observability_ == RegionObservability::kObservable &&
829 !node->op()->HasProperty(Operator::kNoWrite)) {
830 *frame_state = nullptr;
831 frame_state_zapper_ = node;
832 }
833
834 // Remove the end markers of 'atomic' allocation region because the
835 // region should be wired-in now.
836 if (node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kFinishRegion) {
837 // Reset the current region observability.
838 region_observability_ = RegionObservability::kObservable;
839 // Update the value uses to the value input of the finish node and
840 // the effect uses to the effect input.
841 return RemoveRenameNode(node);
842 }
843 if (node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kBeginRegion) {
844 // Determine the observability for this region and use that for all
845 // nodes inside the region (i.e. ignore the absence of kNoWrite on
846 // StoreField and other operators).
847 DCHECK_NE(RegionObservability::kNotObservable, region_observability_)((void) 0);
848 region_observability_ = RegionObservabilityOf(node->op());
849 // Update the value uses to the value input of the finish node and
850 // the effect uses to the effect input.
851 return RemoveRenameNode(node);
852 }
853 if (node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kTypeGuard) {
854 return RemoveRenameNode(node);
855 }
856
857 // Special treatment for checkpoint nodes.
858 if (node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kCheckpoint) {
859 // Unlink the check point; effect uses will be updated to the incoming
860 // effect that is passed. The frame state is preserved for lowering.
861 DCHECK_EQ(RegionObservability::kObservable, region_observability_)((void) 0);
862 *frame_state = NodeProperties::GetFrameStateInput(node);
863 return;
864 }
865
866 // The IfSuccess nodes should always start a basic block (and basic block
867 // start nodes are not handled in the ProcessNode method).
868 DCHECK_NE(IrOpcode::kIfSuccess, node->opcode())((void) 0);
869
870 UpdateEffectControlForNode(node);
871
872 gasm()->AddNode(node);
873
874 if (node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kUnreachable) {
875 // Break the effect chain on {Unreachable} and reconnect to the graph end.
876 // Mark the following code for deletion by connecting to the {Dead} node.
877 gasm()->ConnectUnreachableToEnd();
878 }

1377Node* EffectControlLinearizer::LowerChangeFloat64ToTagged(Node* node) {
1378 CheckForMinusZeroMode mode = CheckMinusZeroModeOf(node->op());
1379 Node* value = node->InputAt(0);
1380
1381 auto done = __ MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
1382 auto if_heapnumber = __ MakeDeferredLabel();
1383 auto if_int32 = __ MakeLabel();
1384
1385 Node* value32 = __ RoundFloat64ToInt32(value);
1386 __ GotoIf(__ Float64Equal(value, __ ChangeInt32ToFloat64(value32)),
1387 &if_int32);
1388 __ Goto(&if_heapnumber);
1389
1390 __ Bind(&if_int32);
1391 {
1392 if (mode == CheckForMinusZeroMode::kCheckForMinusZero) {
1393 Node* zero = __ Int32Constant(0);
1394 auto if_zero = __ MakeDeferredLabel();
1395 auto if_smi = __ MakeLabel();
1396
1397 __ GotoIf(__ Word32Equal(value32, zero), &if_zero);
1398 __ Goto(&if_smi);
1399
1400 __ Bind(&if_zero);
1401 {
1402 // In case of 0, we need to check the high bits for the IEEE -0 pattern.
1403 __ GotoIf(__ Int32LessThan(__ Float64ExtractHighWord32(value), zero),
1404 &if_heapnumber);
1405 __ Goto(&if_smi);
1406 }
1407
1408 __ Bind(&if_smi);
1409 }
1410
1411 if (SmiValuesAre32Bits()) {
1412 Node* value_smi = ChangeInt32ToSmi(value32);
1413 __ Goto(&done, value_smi);
1414 } else {
1415 SmiTagOrOverflow(value32, &if_heapnumber, &done);
1416 }
1417 }
1418
1419 __ Bind(&if_heapnumber);
1420 {
1421 Node* value_number = AllocateHeapNumberWithValue(value);
1422 __ Goto(&done, value_number);
1423 }
1424
1425 __ Bind(&done);
1426 return done.PhiAt(0);

1554
1555void EffectControlLinearizer::TruncateTaggedPointerToBit(
1556 Node* node, GraphAssemblerLabel<1>* done) {
1557 Node* value = node->InputAt(0);
1558
1559 auto if_heapnumber = __ MakeDeferredLabel();
1560 auto if_bigint = __ MakeDeferredLabel();
1561
1562 Node* zero = __ Int32Constant(0);
1563 Node* fzero = __ Float64Constant(0.0);
1564
1565 // Check if {value} is false.
1566 __ GotoIf(__ TaggedEqual(value, __ FalseConstant()), done, zero);
1567
1568 // Check if {value} is the empty string.
1569 __ GotoIf(__ TaggedEqual(value, __ EmptyStringConstant()), done, zero);
1570
1571 // Load the map of {value}.
1572 Node* value_map = __ LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMap(), value);
1573
1574 // Check if the {value} is undetectable and immediately return false.
1575 // This includes undefined and null.
1576 Node* value_map_bitfield =
1577 __ LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMapBitField(), value_map);
1578 __ GotoIfNot(
1579 __ Word32Equal(
1580 __ Word32And(value_map_bitfield,
1581 __ Int32Constant(Map::Bits1::IsUndetectableBit::kMask)),
1582 zero),
1583 done, zero);
1584
1585 // Check if {value} is a HeapNumber.
1586 __ GotoIf(__ TaggedEqual(value_map, __ HeapNumberMapConstant()),
1587 &if_heapnumber);
1588
1589 // Check if {value} is a BigInt.
1590 __ GotoIf(__ TaggedEqual(value_map, __ BigIntMapConstant()), &if_bigint);
1591
1592 // All other values that reach here are true.
1593 __ Goto(done, __ Int32Constant(1));
1594
1595 __ Bind(&if_heapnumber);
1596 {
1597 // For HeapNumber {value}, just check that its value is not 0.0, -0.0 or
1598 // NaN.
1599 Node* value_value =
1600 __ LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForHeapNumberValue(), value);
1601 __ Goto(done, __ Float64LessThan(fzero, __ Float64Abs(value_value)));
1602 }
1603
1604 __ Bind(&if_bigint);
1605 {
1606 Node* bitfield = __ LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForBigIntBitfield(), value);
1607 Node* length_is_zero = __ Word32Equal(
1608 __ Word32And(bitfield, __ Int32Constant(BigInt::LengthBits::kMask)),
1609 __ Int32Constant(0));
1610 __ Goto(done, __ Word32Equal(length_is_zero, zero));
1611 }
1612}

1620

1622
1623 __ Bind(&if_smi);

1626 __ Goto(&done, __ Word32Equal(__ TaggedEqual(value, __ SmiConstant(0)),

1628 }

1762Node* EffectControlLinearizer::LowerCheckClosure(Node* node,
1763 Node* frame_state) {
1764 Handle<FeedbackCell> feedback_cell = FeedbackCellOf(node->op());
1765 Node* value = node->InputAt(0);
1766
1767 // Check that {value} is actually a JSFunction.
1768 Node* value_map = __ LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMap(), value);
1769 Node* value_instance_type =
1770 __ LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMapInstanceType(), value_map);
1771 Node* check_instance_type =
1772 __ Word32Equal(value_instance_type, __ Int32Constant(JS_FUNCTION_TYPE));

1774 check_instance_type, frame_state);
1775
1776 // Check that the {value}s feedback vector cell matches the one
1777 // we recorded before.
1778 Node* value_cell =
1779 __ LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSFunctionFeedbackCell(), value);
1780 Node* check_cell = __ WordEqual(value_cell, __ HeapConstant(feedback_cell));
1781 __ DeoptimizeIfNot(DeoptimizeReason::kWrongFeedbackCell, FeedbackSource(),
1782 check_cell, frame_state);
1783 return value;

1786void EffectControlLinearizer::MigrateInstanceOrDeopt(
1787 Node* value, Node* value_map, Node* frame_state,
1788 FeedbackSource const& feedback_source, DeoptimizeReason reason) {
1789 // If map is not deprecated the migration attempt does not make sense.
1790 Node* bitfield3 = __ LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMapBitField3(), value_map);
1791 Node* is_not_deprecated = __ Word32Equal(
1792 __ Word32And(bitfield3,
1793 __ Int32Constant(Map::Bits3::IsDeprecatedBit::kMask)),
1794 __ Int32Constant(0));
1795 __ DeoptimizeIf(reason, feedback_source, is_not_deprecated, frame_state,
1796 IsSafetyCheck::kCriticalSafetyCheck);
1797 Operator::Properties properties = Operator::kNoDeopt | Operator::kNoThrow;
1798 Runtime::FunctionId id = Runtime::kTryMigrateInstance;
1799 auto call_descriptor = Linkage::GetRuntimeCallDescriptor(
1800 graph()->zone(), id, 1, properties, CallDescriptor::kNoFlags);
1801 Node* result = __ Call(call_descriptor, __ CEntryStubConstant(1), value,
1802 __ ExternalConstant(ExternalReference::Create(id)),
1803 __ Int32Constant(1), __ NoContextConstant());
1804 Node* check = ObjectIsSmi(result);
1805 __ DeoptimizeIf(DeoptimizeReason::kInstanceMigrationFailed, feedback_source,
1806 check, frame_state, IsSafetyCheck::kCriticalSafetyCheck);
1807}

1809void EffectControlLinearizer::LowerCheckMaps(Node* node, Node* frame_state) {
1810 CheckMapsParameters const& p = CheckMapsParametersOf(node->op());
1811 Node* value = node->InputAt(0);
1812
1813 ZoneHandleSet<Map> const& maps = p.maps();
1814 size_t const map_count = maps.size();
1815
1816 if (p.flags() & CheckMapsFlag::kTryMigrateInstance) {
1817 auto done = __ MakeLabel();
1818 auto migrate = __ MakeDeferredLabel();
1819
1820 // Load the current map of the {value}.
1821 Node* value_map = __ LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMap(), value);
1822
1823 // Perform the map checks.
1824 for (size_t i = 0; i < map_count; ++i) {
1825 Node* map = __ HeapConstant(maps[i]);
1826 Node* check = __ TaggedEqual(value_map, map);
1827 if (i == map_count - 1) {
1828 __ BranchWithCriticalSafetyCheck(check, &done, &migrate);
1829 } else {
1830 auto next_map = __ MakeLabel();
1831 __ BranchWithCriticalSafetyCheck(check, &done, &next_map);
1832 __ Bind(&next_map);
1833 }
1834 }
1835
1836 // Perform the (deferred) instance migration.
1837 __ Bind(&migrate);
1838 MigrateInstanceOrDeopt(value, value_map, frame_state, p.feedback(),
1839 DeoptimizeReason::kWrongMap);
1840
1841 // Reload the current map of the {value}.
1842 value_map = __ LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMap(), value);
1843
1844 // Perform the map checks again.
1845 for (size_t i = 0; i < map_count; ++i) {
1846 Node* map = __ HeapConstant(maps[i]);
1847 Node* check = __ TaggedEqual(value_map, map);
1848 if (i == map_count - 1) {
1849 __ DeoptimizeIfNot(DeoptimizeReason::kWrongMap, p.feedback(), check,
1850 frame_state, IsSafetyCheck::kCriticalSafetyCheck);
1851 } else {
1852 auto next_map = __ MakeLabel();
1853 __ BranchWithCriticalSafetyCheck(check, &done, &next_map);
1854 __ Bind(&next_map);
1855 }
1856 }
1857
1858 __ Goto(&done);
1859 __ Bind(&done);
1860 } else {
1861 auto done = __ MakeLabel();
1862
1863 // Load the current map of the {value}.
1864 Node* value_map = __ LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMap(), value);
1865
1866 for (size_t i = 0; i < map_count; ++i) {
1867 Node* map = __ HeapConstant(maps[i]);
1868 Node* check = __ TaggedEqual(value_map, map);
1869
1870 if (i == map_count - 1) {
1871 __ DeoptimizeIfNot(DeoptimizeReason::kWrongMap, p.feedback(), check,
1872 frame_state, IsSafetyCheck::kCriticalSafetyCheck);
1873 } else {
1874 auto next_map = __ MakeLabel();
1875 __ BranchWithCriticalSafetyCheck(check, &done, &next_map);
1876 __ Bind(&next_map);
1877 }
1878 }
1879 __ Goto(&done);
1880 __ Bind(&done);
1881 }
1882}

1884void EffectControlLinearizer::CheckPolymorphic(Node* feedback_slot,
1885 Node* value_map, Node* handler,
1886 GraphAssemblerLabel<0>* done,
1887 Node* frame_state) {
1888 Node* feedback_slot_map =
1889 __ LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMap(), feedback_slot);
1890 Node* is_weak_fixed_array_check =
1891 __ TaggedEqual(feedback_slot_map, __ WeakFixedArrayMapConstant());
1892 __ DeoptimizeIfNot(DeoptimizeReason::kTransitionedToMegamorphicIC,
1893 FeedbackSource(), is_weak_fixed_array_check, frame_state,
1894 IsSafetyCheck::kCriticalSafetyCheck);
1895
1896 Node* length = ChangeSmiToInt32(
1897 __ LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForWeakFixedArrayLength(), feedback_slot));
1898 auto loop = __ MakeLoopLabel(MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
1899 __ Goto(&loop, __ Int32Constant(0));
1900 __ Bind(&loop);
1901 {
1902 Node* index = loop.PhiAt(0);
1903 Node* check = __ Int32LessThan(index, length);
1904 __ DeoptimizeIfNot(DeoptimizeKind::kBailout, DeoptimizeReason::kMissingMap,
1905 FeedbackSource(), check, frame_state,
1906 IsSafetyCheck::kCriticalSafetyCheck);
1907
1908 Node* maybe_map = __ LoadElement(AccessBuilder::ForWeakFixedArrayElement(),
1909 feedback_slot, index);
1910 auto continue_loop = __ MakeLabel();
1911
1912 __ GotoIfNot(BuildIsWeakReferenceTo(maybe_map, value_map), &continue_loop);
1913 constexpr int kHandlerOffsetInEntry = 1;
1914 Node* maybe_handler = __ LoadElement(
1915 AccessBuilder::ForWeakFixedArrayElement(), feedback_slot,
1916 __ Int32Add(index, __ Int32Constant(kHandlerOffsetInEntry)));
1917 Node* handler_check = __ TaggedEqual(maybe_handler, handler);
1918 __ DeoptimizeIfNot(DeoptimizeReason::kWrongHandler, FeedbackSource(),
1919 handler_check, frame_state,
1920 IsSafetyCheck::kCriticalSafetyCheck);
1921
1922 __ Goto(done);
1923
1924 __ Bind(&continue_loop);
1925 constexpr int kEntrySize = 2;
1926 index = __ Int32Add(index, __ Int32Constant(kEntrySize));
1927 __ Goto(&loop, index);
1928 }
1929}

1931void EffectControlLinearizer::ProcessMonomorphic(Node* handler,
1932 GraphAssemblerLabel<0>* done,
1933 Node* frame_state, int slot,
1934 Node* vector) {
1935 Node* feedback_slot_handler =
1936 __ LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForFeedbackVectorSlot(slot + 1), vector);
1937 Node* handler_check = __ TaggedEqual(handler, feedback_slot_handler);
1938 __ DeoptimizeIfNot(DeoptimizeReason::kWrongHandler, FeedbackSource(),
1939 handler_check, frame_state,
1940 IsSafetyCheck::kCriticalSafetyCheck);
1941 __ Goto(done);
1942}

1944void EffectControlLinearizer::BranchOnICState(
1945 int slot_index, Node* vector, Node* value_map, Node* frame_state,
1946 GraphAssemblerLabel<0>* monomorphic, GraphAssemblerLabel<0>* maybe_poly,
1947 GraphAssemblerLabel<0>* migrate, Node** strong_feedback,
1948 Node** poly_array) {
1949 Node* feedback =
1950 __ LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForFeedbackVectorSlot(slot_index), vector);
1951
1952 Node* mono_check = BuildIsWeakReferenceTo(feedback, value_map);
1953 __ GotoIf(mono_check, monomorphic);
1954
1955 Node* is_strong_ref = BuildIsStrongReference(feedback);
1956 if (migrate != nullptr) {
1957 auto check_poly = __ MakeLabel();
1958
1959 __ GotoIf(is_strong_ref, &check_poly);
1960 Node* is_cleared = BuildIsClearedWeakReference(feedback);
1961 __ DeoptimizeIf(DeoptimizeKind::kBailout, DeoptimizeReason::kMissingMap,
1962 FeedbackSource(), is_cleared, frame_state,
1963 IsSafetyCheck::kCriticalSafetyCheck);
1964 *strong_feedback = BuildStrongReferenceFromWeakReference(feedback);
1965 __ Goto(migrate);
1966
1967 __ Bind(&check_poly);
1968 } else {
1969 __ DeoptimizeIfNot(DeoptimizeKind::kBailout, DeoptimizeReason::kMissingMap,
1970 FeedbackSource(), is_strong_ref, frame_state,
1971 IsSafetyCheck::kCriticalSafetyCheck);
1972 }
1973
1974 *poly_array = feedback;
1975 __ Goto(maybe_poly);
1976}

1978void EffectControlLinearizer::LowerDynamicCheckMaps(Node* node,
1979 Node* frame_state) {
1980 DynamicCheckMapsParameters const& p =
1981 DynamicCheckMapsParametersOf(node->op());
1982 Node* value = node->InputAt(0);
1983
1984 FeedbackSource const& feedback = p.feedback();
1985 Node* vector = __ HeapConstant(feedback.vector);
1986 Node* value_map = __ LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMap(), value);
1987 Node* handler = p.handler()->IsSmi()
1988 ? __ SmiConstant(Smi::ToInt(*p.handler()))
1989 : __ HeapConstant(Handle<HeapObject>::cast(p.handler()));
1990
1991 auto done = __ MakeLabel();
1992
1993 // Emit monomorphic checks only if current state is monomorphic. In
1994 // case the current state is polymorphic, and if we ever go back to
1995 // monomorphic start, we will deopt and reoptimize the code.
1996 if (p.state() == DynamicCheckMapsParameters::kMonomorphic) {
1997 auto monomorphic_map_match = __ MakeLabel();
1998 auto maybe_poly = __ MakeLabel();
1999 Node* strong_feedback;
2000 Node* poly_array;
2001
2002 if (p.flags() & CheckMapsFlag::kTryMigrateInstance) {
2003 auto map_check_failed = __ MakeDeferredLabel();
2004 BranchOnICState(feedback.index(), vector, value_map, frame_state,
2005 &monomorphic_map_match, &maybe_poly, &map_check_failed,
2006 &strong_feedback, &poly_array);
2007
2008 __ Bind(&map_check_failed);
2009 {
2010 MigrateInstanceOrDeopt(value, value_map, frame_state, FeedbackSource(),
2011 DeoptimizeReason::kMissingMap);
2012
2013 // Check if new map matches.
2014 Node* new_value_map = __ LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMap(), value);
2015 Node* mono_check = __ TaggedEqual(strong_feedback, new_value_map);
2016 __ DeoptimizeIfNot(DeoptimizeKind::kBailout,
2017 DeoptimizeReason::kMissingMap, FeedbackSource(),
2018 mono_check, frame_state,
2019 IsSafetyCheck::kCriticalSafetyCheck);
2020 ProcessMonomorphic(handler, &done, frame_state, feedback.index(),
2021 vector);
2022 }
2023 } else {
2024 BranchOnICState(feedback.index(), vector, value_map, frame_state,
2025 &monomorphic_map_match, &maybe_poly, nullptr,
2026 &strong_feedback, &poly_array);
2027 }
2028
2029 __ Bind(&monomorphic_map_match);
2030 ProcessMonomorphic(handler, &done, frame_state, feedback.index(), vector);
2031
2032 __ Bind(&maybe_poly);
2033 // TODO(mythria): ICs don't drop deprecated maps from feedback vector.
2034 // So it is not equired to migrate the instance for polymorphic case.
2035 // When we change dynamic map checks to check only four maps re-evaluate
2036 // if this is required.
2037 CheckPolymorphic(poly_array, value_map, handler, &done, frame_state);
2038 } else {
2039 DCHECK_EQ(p.state(), DynamicCheckMapsParameters::kPolymorphic)((void) 0);
2040 Node* feedback_slot = __ LoadField(
2041 AccessBuilder::ForFeedbackVectorSlot(feedback.index()), vector);
2042 // If the IC state at code generation time is not monomorphic, we don't
2043 // handle monomorphic states and just deoptimize if IC transitions to
2044 // monomorphic. For polymorphic ICs it is not required to migrate deprecated
2045 // maps since ICs don't discard deprecated maps from feedback.
2046 Node* is_poly_or_megamorphic = BuildIsStrongReference(feedback_slot);
2047 __ DeoptimizeIfNot(DeoptimizeReason::kTransitionedToMonomorphicIC,
2048 FeedbackSource(), is_poly_or_megamorphic, frame_state,
2049 IsSafetyCheck::kCriticalSafetyCheck);
2050 CheckPolymorphic(feedback_slot, value_map, handler, &done, frame_state);
2051 }
2052 __ Bind(&done);
2053}

2055Node* EffectControlLinearizer::LowerCompareMaps(Node* node) {
2056 ZoneHandleSet<Map> const& maps = CompareMapsParametersOf(node->op());
2057 size_t const map_count = maps.size();
2058 Node* value = node->InputAt(0);
2059
2060 auto done = __ MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kBit);
2061
2062 // Load the current map of the {value}.
2063 Node* value_map = __ LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMap(), value);
2064
2065 for (size_t i = 0; i < map_count; ++i) {
2066 Node* map = __ HeapConstant(maps[i]);
2067 Node* check = __ TaggedEqual(value_map, map);
2068
2069 auto next_map = __ MakeLabel();
2070 auto passed = __ MakeLabel();
2071 __ BranchWithCriticalSafetyCheck(check, &passed, &next_map);
2072
2073 __ Bind(&passed);
2074 __ Goto(&done, __ Int32Constant(1));
2075
2076 __ Bind(&next_map);
2077 }
2078 __ Goto(&done, __ Int32Constant(0));
2079
2080 __ Bind(&done);
2081 return done.PhiAt(0);
2082}

2122Node* EffectControlLinearizer::LowerCheckReceiverOrNullOrUndefined(
2123 Node* node, Node* frame_state) {

2128 __ LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMapInstanceType(), value_map);

2237Node* EffectControlLinearizer::LowerCheckedInt32Div(Node* node,
2238 Node* frame_state) {
2239 Node* lhs = node->InputAt(0);
2240 Node* rhs = node->InputAt(1);
2241 Node* zero = __ Int32Constant(0);
2242
2243 // Check if the {rhs} is a known power of two.
2244 Int32Matcher m(rhs);
2245 if (m.IsPowerOf2()) {
2246 // Since we know that {rhs} is a power of two, we can perform a fast
2247 // check to see if the relevant least significant bits of the {lhs}
2248 // are all zero, and if so we know that we can perform a division
2249 // safely (and fast by doing an arithmetic - aka sign preserving -
2250 // right shift on {lhs}).
2251 int32_t divisor = m.Value();
2252 Node* mask = __ Int32Constant(divisor - 1);
2253 Node* shift = __ Int32Constant(base::bits::WhichPowerOfTwo(divisor));
2254 Node* check = __ Word32Equal(__ Word32And(lhs, mask), zero);
2255 __ DeoptimizeIfNot(DeoptimizeReason::kLostPrecision, FeedbackSource(),
2256 check, frame_state);
2257 return __ Word32Sar(lhs, shift);
2258 } else {
2259 auto if_rhs_positive = __ MakeLabel();
2260 auto if_rhs_negative = __ MakeDeferredLabel();
2261 auto done = __ MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
2262
2263 // Check if {rhs} is positive (and not zero).
2264 Node* check_rhs_positive = __ Int32LessThan(zero, rhs);
2265 __ Branch(check_rhs_positive, &if_rhs_positive, &if_rhs_negative);
2266
2267 __ Bind(&if_rhs_positive);
2268 {
2269 // Fast case, no additional checking required.
2270 __ Goto(&done, __ Int32Div(lhs, rhs));
2271 }
2272
2273 __ Bind(&if_rhs_negative);
2274 {
2275 auto if_lhs_minint = __ MakeDeferredLabel();
2276 auto if_lhs_notminint = __ MakeLabel();
2277
2278 // Check if {rhs} is zero.
2279 Node* check_rhs_zero = __ Word32Equal(rhs, zero);
2280 __ DeoptimizeIf(DeoptimizeReason::kDivisionByZero, FeedbackSource(),
2281 check_rhs_zero, frame_state);
2282
2283 // Check if {lhs} is zero, as that would produce minus zero.
2284 Node* check_lhs_zero = __ Word32Equal(lhs, zero);
2285 __ DeoptimizeIf(DeoptimizeReason::kMinusZero, FeedbackSource(),
2286 check_lhs_zero, frame_state);
2287
2288 // Check if {lhs} is kMinInt and {rhs} is -1, in which case we'd have
2289 // to return -kMinInt, which is not representable as Word32.
2290 Node* check_lhs_minint = __ Word32Equal(lhs, __ Int32Constant(kMinInt));
2291 __ Branch(check_lhs_minint, &if_lhs_minint, &if_lhs_notminint);
2292
2293 __ Bind(&if_lhs_minint);
2294 {
2295 // Check that {rhs} is not -1, otherwise result would be -kMinInt.
2296 Node* check_rhs_minusone = __ Word32Equal(rhs, __ Int32Constant(-1));
2297 __ DeoptimizeIf(DeoptimizeReason::kOverflow, FeedbackSource(),
2298 check_rhs_minusone, frame_state);
2299
2300 // Perform the actual integer division.
2301 __ Goto(&done, __ Int32Div(lhs, rhs));
2302 }
2303
2304 __ Bind(&if_lhs_notminint);
2305 {
2306 // Perform the actual integer division.
2307 __ Goto(&done, __ Int32Div(lhs, rhs));
2308 }
2309 }
2310
2311 __ Bind(&done);
2312 Node* value = done.PhiAt(0);
2313
2314 // Check if the remainder is non-zero.
2315 Node* check = __ Word32Equal(lhs, __ Int32Mul(value, rhs));
2316 __ DeoptimizeIfNot(DeoptimizeReason::kLostPrecision, FeedbackSource(),
2317 check, frame_state);
2318
2319 return value;
2320 }

2323template <size_t VarCount, size_t VarCount2>
2324void EffectControlLinearizer::SmiTagOrOverflow(
2325 Node* value, GraphAssemblerLabel<VarCount>* if_overflow,
2326 GraphAssemblerLabel<VarCount2>* done) {
2327 DCHECK(SmiValuesAre31Bits())((void) 0);
2328 // Check for overflow at the same time that we are smi tagging.
2329 // Since smi tagging shifts left by one, it's the same as adding value twice.
2330 Node* add = __ Int32AddWithOverflow(value, value);
2331 Node* ovf = __ Projection(1, add);
2332 __ GotoIf(ovf, if_overflow);
2333 Node* value_smi = __ Projection(0, add);
2334 value_smi = ChangeTaggedInt32ToSmi(value_smi);
2335 __ Goto(done, value_smi);
2336}

2344 Node* add = __ Int32AddWithOverflow(value, value);
2345 Node* check = __ Projection(1, add);
2346 __ DeoptimizeIf(DeoptimizeReason::kLostPrecision, params.feedback(), check,
2347 frame_state);
2348 Node* result = __ Projection(0, add);

2352Node* EffectControlLinearizer::BuildUint32Mod(Node* lhs, Node* rhs) {
2353 auto if_rhs_power_of_two = __ MakeLabel();
2354 auto done = __ MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
2355
2356 // Compute the mask for the {rhs}.
2357 Node* one = __ Int32Constant(1);
2358 Node* msk = __ Int32Sub(rhs, one);
2359
2360 // Check if the {rhs} is a power of two.
2361 __ GotoIf(__ Word32Equal(__ Word32And(rhs, msk), __ Int32Constant(0)),
2362 &if_rhs_power_of_two);
2363 {
2364 // The {rhs} is not a power of two, do a generic Uint32Mod.
2365 __ Goto(&done, __ Uint32Mod(lhs, rhs));
2366 }
2367
2368 __ Bind(&if_rhs_power_of_two);
2369 {
2370 // The {rhs} is a power of two, just do a fast bit masking.
2371 __ Goto(&done, __ Word32And(lhs, msk));
2372 }
2373
2374 __ Bind(&done);
2375 return done.PhiAt(0);
2376}

2378Node* EffectControlLinearizer::LowerCheckedInt32Mod(Node* node,
2379 Node* frame_state) {
2380 // General case for signed integer modulus, with optimization for (unknown)
2381 // power of 2 right hand side.
2382 //
2383 // if rhs <= 0 then
2384 // rhs = -rhs
2385 // deopt if rhs == 0
2386 // let msk = rhs - 1 in
2387 // if lhs < 0 then
2388 // let lhs_abs = -lsh in
2389 // let res = if rhs & msk == 0 then
2390 // lhs_abs & msk
2391 // else
2392 // lhs_abs % rhs in
2393 // if lhs < 0 then
2394 // deopt if res == 0
2395 // -res
2396 // else
2397 // res
2398 // else
2399 // if rhs & msk == 0 then
2400 // lhs & msk
2401 // else
2402 // lhs % rhs
2403 //
2404 Node* lhs = node->InputAt(0);
2405 Node* rhs = node->InputAt(1);
2406
2407 auto if_rhs_not_positive = __ MakeDeferredLabel();
2408 auto if_lhs_negative = __ MakeDeferredLabel();
2409 auto if_rhs_power_of_two = __ MakeLabel();
2410 auto rhs_checked = __ MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
2411 auto done = __ MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
2412
2413 Node* zero = __ Int32Constant(0);
2414
2415 // Check if {rhs} is not strictly positive.
2416 Node* check0 = __ Int32LessThanOrEqual(rhs, zero);
2417 __ GotoIf(check0, &if_rhs_not_positive);
2418 __ Goto(&rhs_checked, rhs);
2419
2420 __ Bind(&if_rhs_not_positive);
2421 {
2422 // Negate {rhs}, might still produce a negative result in case of
2423 // -2^31, but that is handled safely below.
2424 Node* vtrue0 = __ Int32Sub(zero, rhs);
2425
2426 // Ensure that {rhs} is not zero, otherwise we'd have to return NaN.
2427 __ DeoptimizeIf(DeoptimizeReason::kDivisionByZero, FeedbackSource(),
2428 __ Word32Equal(vtrue0, zero), frame_state);
2429 __ Goto(&rhs_checked, vtrue0);
2430 }
2431
2432 __ Bind(&rhs_checked);
2433 rhs = rhs_checked.PhiAt(0);
2434
2435 __ GotoIf(__ Int32LessThan(lhs, zero), &if_lhs_negative);
2436 {
2437 // The {lhs} is a non-negative integer.
2438 __ Goto(&done, BuildUint32Mod(lhs, rhs));
2439 }
2440
2441 __ Bind(&if_lhs_negative);
2442 {
2443 // The {lhs} is a negative integer. This is very unlikely and
2444 // we intentionally don't use the BuildUint32Mod() here, which
2445 // would try to figure out whether {rhs} is a power of two,
2446 // since this is intended to be a slow-path.
2447 Node* res = __ Uint32Mod(__ Int32Sub(zero, lhs), rhs);
2448
2449 // Check if we would have to return -0.
2450 __ DeoptimizeIf(DeoptimizeReason::kMinusZero, FeedbackSource(),
2451 __ Word32Equal(res, zero), frame_state);
2452 __ Goto(&done, __ Int32Sub(zero, res));
2453 }
2454
2455 __ Bind(&done);
2456 return done.PhiAt(0);
2457}

2460 Node* frame_state) {
2461 Node* lhs = node->InputAt(0);
2462 Node* rhs = node->InputAt(1);
2463 Node* zero = __ Int32Constant(0);
2464
2465 // Check if the {rhs} is a known power of two.
2466 Uint32Matcher m(rhs);
2467 if (m.IsPowerOf2()) {
2468 // Since we know that {rhs} is a power of two, we can perform a fast
2469 // check to see if the relevant least significant bits of the {lhs}

2471 // safely (and fast by doing a logical - aka zero extending - right

2793Node* EffectControlLinearizer::LowerCheckedTaggedToArrayIndex(
2794 Node* node, Node* frame_state) {
2795 CheckParameters const& params = CheckParametersOf(node->op());
2796 Node* value = node->InputAt(0);
2797
2798 auto if_not_smi = __ MakeDeferredLabel();
2799 auto done = __ MakeLabel(MachineType::PointerRepresentation());
2800
2801 __ GotoIfNot(ObjectIsSmi(value), &if_not_smi);
2802 // In the Smi case, just convert to intptr_t.
2803 __ Goto(&done, ChangeSmiToIntPtr(value));
2804
2805 // In the non-Smi case, check the heap numberness, load the number and convert
2806 // to integer.
2807 __ Bind(&if_not_smi);

2811 __ GotoIfNot(is_heap_number, &if_not_heap_number);
2812
2813 Node* number = __ LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForHeapNumberValue(), value);
2814 number = BuildCheckedFloat64ToIndex(params.feedback(), number, frame_state);
2815 __ Goto(&done, number);
2816
2817 __ Bind(&if_not_heap_number);
2818 auto calculate_index = __ MakeDeferredLabel();
2819 Node* value_instance_type =
2820 __ LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMapInstanceType(), value_map);
2821 Node* is_string = __ Uint32LessThan(value_instance_type,
2822 __ Uint32Constant(FIRST_NONSTRING_TYPE));
2823 __ DeoptimizeIfNot(DeoptimizeReason::kNotAString, params.feedback(),
2824 is_string, frame_state);
2825
2826 MachineSignature::Builder builder(graph()->zone(), 1, 1);
2827 builder.AddReturn(MachineType::IntPtr());
2828 builder.AddParam(MachineType::TaggedPointer());
2829 Node* string_to_array_index_function =
2830 __ ExternalConstant(ExternalReference::string_to_array_index_function());
2831 auto call_descriptor =
2832 Linkage::GetSimplifiedCDescriptor(graph()->zone(), builder.Build());
2833 Node* index = __ Call(common()->Call(call_descriptor),
2834 string_to_array_index_function, value);
2835
2836 __ DeoptimizeIf(DeoptimizeReason::kNotAnArrayIndex, params.feedback(),
2837 __ Word32Equal(index, __ Int32Constant(-1)), frame_state);
2838
2839 __ Goto(&done, index);
2840
2841 __ Bind(&done);
2842 return done.PhiAt(0);
2843}

3427// There is no (currently) available constexpr version of bit_cast, so we have
3428// to make do with constructing the -0.0 bits manually (by setting the sign bit
3429// to 1 and everything else to 0).
3430// TODO(leszeks): Revisit when upgrading to C++20.
3431constexpr int32_t kMinusZeroLoBits = static_cast<int32_t>(0);
3432constexpr int32_t kMinusZeroHiBits = static_cast<int32_t>(1) << 31;
3433constexpr int64_t kMinusZeroBits =
3434 (static_cast<uint64_t>(kMinusZeroHiBits) << 32) | kMinusZeroLoBits;
3435
3436} // namespace

3438Node* EffectControlLinearizer::LowerObjectIsMinusZero(Node* node) {
3439 Node* value = node->InputAt(0);
3440 Node* zero = __ Int32Constant(0);
3441
3442 auto done = __ MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kBit);
3443
3444 // Check if {value} is a Smi.
3445 __ GotoIf(ObjectIsSmi(value), &done, zero);
3446
3447 // Check if {value} is a HeapNumber.
3448 Node* value_map = __ LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMap(), value);
3449 __ GotoIfNot(__ TaggedEqual(value_map, __ HeapNumberMapConstant()), &done,
3450 zero);
3451
3452 // Check if {value} contains -0.
3453 Node* value_value = __ LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForHeapNumberValue(), value);
3454 if (machine()->Is64()) {
3455 Node* value64 = __ BitcastFloat64ToInt64(value_value);
3456 __ Goto(&done, __ Word64Equal(value64, __ Int64Constant(kMinusZeroBits)));

3460 &done, zero);
3461 Node* value_hi = __ Float64ExtractHighWord32(value_value);
3462 __ Goto(&done,
3463 __ Word32Equal(value_hi, __ Int32Constant(kMinusZeroHiBits)));
3464 }
3465
3466 __ Bind(&done);

3718Node* EffectControlLinearizer::LowerArgumentsLength(Node* node) {

3720 int formal_parameter_count = FormalParameterCountOf(node->op());
3721 DCHECK_LE(0, formal_parameter_count)((void) 0);
3722
3723 // The ArgumentsLength node is computing the actual number of arguments.
3724 // We have to distinguish the case when there is an arguments adaptor frame
3725 // (i.e., arguments_frame != LoadFramePointer()).
3726 auto if_adaptor_frame = __ MakeLabel();

3728

3731 __ SmiConstant(formal_parameter_count));
3732 __ Goto(&if_adaptor_frame);
3733
3734 __ Bind(&if_adaptor_frame);
3735 Node* arguments_length = __ BitcastWordToTaggedSigned(__ Load(
3736 MachineType::Pointer(), arguments_frame,
3737 __ IntPtrConstant(ArgumentsAdaptorFrameConstants::kLengthOffset)));
3738 __ Goto(&done, arguments_length);
3739
3740 __ Bind(&done);
3741 return done.PhiAt(0);

3744Node* EffectControlLinearizer::LowerRestLength(Node* node) {
3745 Node* arguments_frame = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 0);
3746 int formal_parameter_count = FormalParameterCountOf(node->op());
3747 DCHECK_LE(0, formal_parameter_count)((void) 0);
3748
3749 // The RestLength node is computing the number of rest parameters,
3750 // which is max(0, actual_parameter_count - formal_parameter_count).
3751 // We have to distinguish the case, when there is an arguments adaptor frame
3752 // (i.e., arguments_frame != LoadFramePointer()).
3753 auto if_adaptor_frame = __ MakeLabel();
3754 auto done = __ MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kTaggedSigned);
3755
3756 Node* frame = __ LoadFramePointer();
3757 __ GotoIf(__ TaggedEqual(arguments_frame, frame), &done, __ SmiConstant(0));
3758 __ Goto(&if_adaptor_frame);
3759

3761 Node* arguments_length = __ BitcastWordToTaggedSigned(__ Load(
3762 MachineType::Pointer(), arguments_frame,
3763 __ IntPtrConstant(ArgumentsAdaptorFrameConstants::kLengthOffset)));
3764
3765 Node* rest_length =
3766 __ SmiSub(arguments_length, __ SmiConstant(formal_parameter_count));
3767 __ GotoIf(__ SmiLessThan(rest_length, __ SmiConstant(0)), &done,
3768 __ SmiConstant(0));
3769 __ Goto(&done, rest_length);
3770
3771 __ Bind(&done);
3772 return done.PhiAt(0);

3796Node* EffectControlLinearizer::LowerNewDoubleElements(Node* node) {
3797 AllocationType const allocation = AllocationTypeOf(node->op());
3798 Node* length = node->InputAt(0);
3799
3800 auto done = __ MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
3801 Node* zero_length = __ IntPtrEqual(length, __ IntPtrConstant(0));
3802 __ GotoIf(zero_length, &done,
3803 __ HeapConstant(factory()->empty_fixed_array()));
3804
3805 // Compute the effective size of the backing store.
3806 Node* size = __ IntAdd(__ WordShl(length, __ IntPtrConstant(kDoubleSizeLog2)),
3807 __ IntPtrConstant(FixedDoubleArray::kHeaderSize));
3808
3809 // Allocate the result and initialize the header.
3810 Node* result = __ Allocate(allocation, size);
3811 __ StoreField(AccessBuilder::ForMap(), result,
3812 __ FixedDoubleArrayMapConstant());
3813 __ StoreField(AccessBuilder::ForFixedArrayLength(), result,
3814 ChangeIntPtrToSmi(length));
3815
3816 // Initialize the backing store with holes.
3817 STATIC_ASSERT_FIELD_OFFSETS_EQUAL(HeapNumber::kValueOffset,static_assert(static_cast<int>(HeapNumber::kValueOffset
) == Oddball::kToNumberRawOffset, "static_cast<int>(HeapNumber::kValueOffset) == Oddball::kToNumberRawOffset"
)
3818 Oddball::kToNumberRawOffset)static_assert(static_cast<int>(HeapNumber::kValueOffset
) == Oddball::kToNumberRawOffset, "static_cast<int>(HeapNumber::kValueOffset) == Oddball::kToNumberRawOffset"
);
3819 Node* the_hole =
3820 __ LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForHeapNumberValue(), __ TheHoleConstant());
3821 auto loop = __ MakeLoopLabel(MachineType::PointerRepresentation());
3822 __ Goto(&loop, __ IntPtrConstant(0));
3823 __ Bind(&loop);
3824 {
3825 // Check if we've initialized everything.
3826 Node* index = loop.PhiAt(0);
3827 Node* check = __ UintLessThan(index, length);
3828 __ GotoIfNot(check, &done, result);
3829
3830 ElementAccess const access = {kTaggedBase, FixedDoubleArray::kHeaderSize,
3831 Type::NumberOrHole(), MachineType::Float64(),
3832 kNoWriteBarrier};
3833 __ StoreElement(access, result, index, the_hole);
3834
3835 // Advance the {index}.
3836 index = __ IntAdd(index, __ IntPtrConstant(1));
3837 __ Goto(&loop, index);
3838 }
3839
3840 __ Bind(&done);
3841 return done.PhiAt(0);

3863 // Initialize the backing store with holes.
3864 Node* the_hole = __ TheHoleConstant();
3865 auto loop = __ MakeLoopLabel(MachineType::PointerRepresentation());
3866 __ Goto(&loop, __ IntPtrConstant(0));
3867 __ Bind(&loop);
3868 {
3869 // Check if we've initialized everything.
3870 Node* index = loop.PhiAt(0);
3871 Node* check = __ UintLessThan(index, length);
3872 __ GotoIfNot(check, &done, result);
3873
3874 // Storing "the_hole" doesn't need a write barrier.
3875 ElementAccess const access = {kTaggedBase, FixedArray::kHeaderSize,
3876 Type::Any(), MachineType::AnyTagged(),
3877 kNoWriteBarrier};
3878 __ StoreElement(access, result, index, the_hole);
3879
3880 // Advance the {index}.
3881 index = __ IntAdd(index, __ IntPtrConstant(1));
3882 __ Goto(&loop, index);
3883 }
3884
3885 __ Bind(&done);
3886 return done.PhiAt(0);
3887}

3918Node* EffectControlLinearizer::LowerNewConsString(Node* node) {
3919 Node* length = node->InputAt(0);
3920 Node* first = node->InputAt(1);
3921 Node* second = node->InputAt(2);
3922
3923 // Determine the instance types of {first} and {second}.
3924 Node* first_map = __ LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMap(), first);
3925 Node* first_instance_type =
3926 __ LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMapInstanceType(), first_map);
3927 Node* second_map = __ LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMap(), second);
3928 Node* second_instance_type =
3929 __ LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMapInstanceType(), second_map);
3930
3931 // Determine the proper map for the resulting ConsString.
3932 // If both {first} and {second} are one-byte strings, we
3933 // create a new ConsOneByteString, otherwise we create a
3934 // new ConsString instead.
3935 auto if_onebyte = __ MakeLabel();
3936 auto if_twobyte = __ MakeLabel();
3937 auto done = __ MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
3938 STATIC_ASSERT(kOneByteStringTag != 0)static_assert(kOneByteStringTag != 0, "kOneByteStringTag != 0"
);
3939 STATIC_ASSERT(kTwoByteStringTag == 0)static_assert(kTwoByteStringTag == 0, "kTwoByteStringTag == 0"
);
3940 Node* instance_type = __ Word32And(first_instance_type, second_instance_type);
3941 Node* encoding =
3942 __ Word32And(instance_type, __ Int32Constant(kStringEncodingMask));
3943 __ Branch(__ Word32Equal(encoding, __ Int32Constant(kTwoByteStringTag)),
3944 &if_twobyte, &if_onebyte);
3945 __ Bind(&if_onebyte);
3946 __ Goto(&done, __ HeapConstant(factory()->cons_one_byte_string_map()));
3947 __ Bind(&if_twobyte);
3948 __ Goto(&done, __ HeapConstant(factory()->cons_string_map()));
3949 __ Bind(&done);
3950 Node* result_map = done.PhiAt(0);
3951
3952 // Allocate the resulting ConsString.
3953 Node* result =
3954 __ Allocate(AllocationType::kYoung, __ IntPtrConstant(ConsString::kSize));
3955 __ StoreField(AccessBuilder::ForMap(), result, result_map);
3956 __ StoreField(AccessBuilder::ForNameHashField(), result,
3957 __ Int32Constant(Name::kEmptyHashField));
3958 __ StoreField(AccessBuilder::ForStringLength(), result, length);
3959 __ StoreField(AccessBuilder::ForConsStringFirst(), result, first);
3960 __ StoreField(AccessBuilder::ForConsStringSecond(), result, second);
3961 return result;
3962}

4042Node* EffectControlLinearizer::LowerStringCharCodeAt(Node* node) {
4043 Node* receiver = node->InputAt(0);
4044 Node* position = node->InputAt(1);
4045
4046 // We need a loop here to properly deal with indirect strings
4047 // (SlicedString, ConsString and ThinString).
4048 auto loop = __ MakeLoopLabel(MachineRepresentation::kTagged,
4049 MachineType::PointerRepresentation());
4050 auto loop_next = __ MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kTagged,
4051 MachineType::PointerRepresentation());
4052 auto loop_done = __ MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
4053 __ Goto(&loop, receiver, position);
4054 __ Bind(&loop);
4055 {
4056 Node* receiver = loop.PhiAt(0);
4057 Node* position = loop.PhiAt(1);
4058 Node* receiver_map = __ LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMap(), receiver);
4059 Node* receiver_instance_type =
4060 __ LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMapInstanceType(), receiver_map);
4061 Node* receiver_representation = __ Word32And(
4062 receiver_instance_type, __ Int32Constant(kStringRepresentationMask));
4063
4064 // Dispatch on the current {receiver}s string representation.
4065 auto if_lessthanoreq_cons = __ MakeLabel();
4066 auto if_greaterthan_cons = __ MakeLabel();
4067 auto if_seqstring = __ MakeLabel();
4068 auto if_consstring = __ MakeLabel();
4069 auto if_thinstring = __ MakeLabel();
4070 auto if_externalstring = __ MakeLabel();
4071 auto if_slicedstring = __ MakeLabel();
4072 auto if_runtime = __ MakeDeferredLabel();
4073
4074 __ Branch(__ Int32LessThanOrEqual(receiver_representation,
4075 __ Int32Constant(kConsStringTag)),
4076 &if_lessthanoreq_cons, &if_greaterthan_cons);
4077
4078 __ Bind(&if_lessthanoreq_cons);
4079 {
4080 __ Branch(__ Word32Equal(receiver_representation,
4081 __ Int32Constant(kConsStringTag)),
4082 &if_consstring, &if_seqstring);
4083 }
4084
4085 __ Bind(&if_greaterthan_cons);
4086 {
4087 __ GotoIf(__ Word32Equal(receiver_representation,
4088 __ Int32Constant(kThinStringTag)),
4089 &if_thinstring);
4090 __ GotoIf(__ Word32Equal(receiver_representation,
4091 __ Int32Constant(kExternalStringTag)),
4092 &if_externalstring);
4093 __ Branch(__ Word32Equal(receiver_representation,
4094 __ Int32Constant(kSlicedStringTag)),
4095 &if_slicedstring, &if_runtime);
4096 }
4097
4098 __ Bind(&if_seqstring);
4099 {
4100 Node* receiver_is_onebyte = __ Word32Equal(
4101 __ Word32Equal(__ Word32And(receiver_instance_type,
4102 __ Int32Constant(kStringEncodingMask)),
4103 __ Int32Constant(kTwoByteStringTag)),
4104 __ Int32Constant(0));
4105 Node* result = LoadFromSeqString(receiver, position, receiver_is_onebyte);
4106 __ Goto(&loop_done, result);
4107 }
4108
4109 __ Bind(&if_consstring);
4110 {
4111 Node* receiver_second =
4112 __ LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForConsStringSecond(), receiver);
4113 __ GotoIfNot(__ TaggedEqual(receiver_second, __ EmptyStringConstant()),
4114 &if_runtime);
4115 Node* receiver_first =
4116 __ LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForConsStringFirst(), receiver);
4117 __ Goto(&loop_next, receiver_first, position);
4118 }
4119
4120 __ Bind(&if_thinstring);
4121 {
4122 Node* receiver_actual =
4123 __ LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForThinStringActual(), receiver);
4124 __ Goto(&loop_next, receiver_actual, position);
4125 }
4126
4127 __ Bind(&if_externalstring);
4128 {
4129 // We need to bailout to the runtime for uncached external strings.
4130 __ GotoIf(__ Word32Equal(
4131 __ Word32And(receiver_instance_type,
4132 __ Int32Constant(kUncachedExternalStringMask)),
4133 __ Int32Constant(kUncachedExternalStringTag)),
4134 &if_runtime);
4135
4136 Node* receiver_data = __ LoadField(
4137 AccessBuilder::ForExternalStringResourceData(), receiver);
4138
4139 auto if_onebyte = __ MakeLabel();
4140 auto if_twobyte = __ MakeLabel();
4141 __ Branch(
4142 __ Word32Equal(__ Word32And(receiver_instance_type,
4143 __ Int32Constant(kStringEncodingMask)),
4144 __ Int32Constant(kTwoByteStringTag)),
4145 &if_twobyte, &if_onebyte);
4146
4147 __ Bind(&if_onebyte);
4148 {
4149 Node* result = __ Load(MachineType::Uint8(), receiver_data, position);
4150 __ Goto(&loop_done, result);
4151 }
4152
4153 __ Bind(&if_twobyte);
4154 {
4155 Node* result = __ Load(MachineType::Uint16(), receiver_data,
4156 __ WordShl(position, __ IntPtrConstant(1)));
4157 __ Goto(&loop_done, result);
4158 }
4159 }
4160
4161 __ Bind(&if_slicedstring);
4162 {
4163 Node* receiver_offset =
4164 __ LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForSlicedStringOffset(), receiver);
4165 Node* receiver_parent =
4166 __ LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForSlicedStringParent(), receiver);
4167 __ Goto(&loop_next, receiver_parent,
4168 __ IntAdd(position, ChangeSmiToIntPtr(receiver_offset)));
4169 }
4170
4171 __ Bind(&if_runtime);
4172 {
4173 Operator::Properties properties = Operator::kNoDeopt | Operator::kNoThrow;
4174 Runtime::FunctionId id = Runtime::kStringCharCodeAt;
4175 auto call_descriptor = Linkage::GetRuntimeCallDescriptor(
4176 graph()->zone(), id, 2, properties, CallDescriptor::kNoFlags);
4177 Node* result = __ Call(call_descriptor, __ CEntryStubConstant(1),
4178 receiver, ChangeIntPtrToSmi(position),
4179 __ ExternalConstant(ExternalReference::Create(id)),
4180 __ Int32Constant(2), __ NoContextConstant());
4181 __ Goto(&loop_done, ChangeSmiToInt32(result));
4182 }
4183
4184 __ Bind(&loop_next);
4185 __ Goto(&loop, loop_next.PhiAt(0), loop_next.PhiAt(1));
4186 }
4187 __ Bind(&loop_done);
4188 return loop_done.PhiAt(0);
4189}

4344Node* EffectControlLinearizer::LowerStringFromSingleCodePoint(Node* node) {

4352
4353 // Check if the {code} is a single code unit
4354 Node* check0 = __ Uint32LessThanOrEqual(code, __ Uint32Constant(0xFFFF));
4355 __ GotoIfNot(check0, &if_not_single_code);
4356
4357 {
4358 // Check if the {code} is a one byte character
4359 Node* check1 = __ Uint32LessThanOrEqual(
4360 code, __ Uint32Constant(String::kMaxOneByteCharCode));
4361 __ GotoIfNot(check1, &if_not_one_byte);

4363 // Load the isolate wide single character string cache.
4364 Node* cache = __ HeapConstant(factory()->single_character_string_cache());
4365

4367 Node* index = machine()->Is32() ? code : __ ChangeUint32ToUint64(code);

4370 // cache already.
4371 Node* entry =
4372 __ LoadElement(AccessBuilder::ForFixedArrayElement(), cache, index);
4373
4374 Node* check2 = __ TaggedEqual(entry, __ UndefinedConstant());
4375 __ GotoIf(check2, &cache_miss);
4376
4377 // Use the {entry} from the {cache}.
4378 __ Goto(&done, entry);
4379
4380 __ Bind(&cache_miss);

4382 // Allocate a new SeqOneByteString for {code}.

4385 __ IntPtrConstant(SeqOneByteString::SizeFor(1)));

4393 StoreRepresentation(MachineRepresentation::kWord8, kNoWriteBarrier),
4394 vtrue2,
4395 __ IntPtrConstant(SeqOneByteString::kHeaderSize - kHeapObjectTag),
4396 code);

4398 // Remember it in the {cache}.
4399 __ StoreElement(AccessBuilder::ForFixedArrayElement(), cache, index,
4400 vtrue2);
4401 __ Goto(&done, vtrue2);
4402 }
4403 }
4404
4405 __ Bind(&if_not_one_byte);
4406 {
4407 // Allocate a new SeqTwoByteString for {code}.
4408 Node* vfalse1 =
4409 __ Allocate(AllocationType::kYoung,
4410 __ IntPtrConstant(SeqTwoByteString::SizeFor(1)));
4411 __ StoreField(AccessBuilder::ForMap(), vfalse1,
4412 __ HeapConstant(factory()->string_map()));
4413 __ StoreField(AccessBuilder::ForNameHashField(), vfalse1,

4425
4426 __ Bind(&if_not_single_code);
4427 // Generate surrogate pair string
4428 {
4429 // Convert UTF32 to UTF16 code units, and store as a 32 bit word.
4430 Node* lead_offset = __ Int32Constant(0xD800 - (0x10000 >> 10));
4431
4432 // lead = (codepoint >> 10) + LEAD_OFFSET
4433 Node* lead =
4434 __ Int32Add(__ Word32Shr(code, __ Int32Constant(10)), lead_offset);
4435
4436 // trail = (codepoint & 0x3FF) + 0xDC00;
4437 Node* trail = __ Int32Add(__ Word32And(code, __ Int32Constant(0x3FF)),
4438 __ Int32Constant(0xDC00));
4439
4440 // codpoint = (trail << 16) | lead;
4441#if V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN
4442 code = __ Word32Or(__ Word32Shl(lead, __ Int32Constant(16)), trail);
4443#else
4444 code = __ Word32Or(__ Word32Shl(trail, __ Int32Constant(16)), lead);
4445#endif
4446
4447 // Allocate a new SeqTwoByteString for {code}.
4448 Node* vfalse0 =
4449 __ Allocate(AllocationType::kYoung,
4450 __ IntPtrConstant(SeqTwoByteString::SizeFor(2)));
4451 __ StoreField(AccessBuilder::ForMap(), vfalse0,
4452 __ HeapConstant(factory()->string_map()));
4453 __ StoreField(AccessBuilder::ForNameHashField(), vfalse0,

4605Node* EffectControlLinearizer::LowerCheckFloat64Hole(Node* node,
4606 Node* frame_state) {
4607 // If we reach this point w/o eliminating the {node} that's marked
4608 // with allow-return-hole, we cannot do anything, so just deoptimize
4609 // in case of the hole NaN.
4610 CheckFloat64HoleParameters const& params =
4611 CheckFloat64HoleParametersOf(node->op());
4612 Node* value = node->InputAt(0);
4613
4614 auto if_nan = __ MakeDeferredLabel();
4615 auto done = __ MakeLabel();
4616
4617 // First check whether {value} is a NaN at all...
4618 __ Branch(__ Float64Equal(value, value), &done, &if_nan);
4619
4620 __ Bind(&if_nan);
4621 {
4622 // ...and only if {value} is a NaN, perform the expensive bit
4623 // check. See http://crbug.com/v8/8264 for details.
4624 Node* check = __ Word32Equal(__ Float64ExtractHighWord32(value),
4625 __ Int32Constant(kHoleNanUpper32));
4626 __ DeoptimizeIf(DeoptimizeReason::kHole, params.feedback(), check,
4627 frame_state);
4628 __ Goto(&done);
4629 }
4630
4631 __ Bind(&done);
4632 return value;
4633}

4661void EffectControlLinearizer::LowerCheckEqualsInternalizedString(
4662 Node* node, Node* frame_state) {
4663 Node* exp = node->InputAt(0);
4664 Node* val = node->InputAt(1);
4665
4666 auto if_same = __ MakeLabel();
4667 auto if_notsame = __ MakeDeferredLabel();
4668 auto if_thinstring = __ MakeLabel();
4669 auto if_notthinstring = __ MakeLabel();
4670
4671 // Check if {exp} and {val} are the same, which is the likely case.
4672 __ Branch(__ TaggedEqual(exp, val), &if_same, &if_notsame);
4673
4674 __ Bind(&if_notsame);
4675 {
4676 // Now {val} could still be a non-internalized String that matches {exp}.
4677 __ DeoptimizeIf(DeoptimizeReason::kWrongName, FeedbackSource(),
4678 ObjectIsSmi(val), frame_state);
4679 Node* val_map = __ LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMap(), val);
4680 Node* val_instance_type =
4681 __ LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMapInstanceType(), val_map);
4682
4683 // Check for the common case of ThinString first.
4684 __ GotoIf(__ Word32Equal(val_instance_type,
4685 __ Int32Constant(THIN_ONE_BYTE_STRING_TYPE)),
4686 &if_thinstring);
4687 __ Branch(
4688 __ Word32Equal(val_instance_type, __ Int32Constant(THIN_STRING_TYPE)),
4689 &if_thinstring, &if_notthinstring);
4690
4691 __ Bind(&if_notthinstring);
4692 {
4693 // Check that the {val} is a non-internalized String, if it's anything
4694 // else it cannot match the recorded feedback {exp} anyways.
4695 __ DeoptimizeIfNot(
4696 DeoptimizeReason::kWrongName, FeedbackSource(),
4697 __ Word32Equal(__ Word32And(val_instance_type,
4698 __ Int32Constant(kIsNotStringMask |
4699 kIsNotInternalizedMask)),
4700 __ Int32Constant(kStringTag | kNotInternalizedTag)),
4701 frame_state);
4702
4703 // Try to find the {val} in the string table.
4704 MachineSignature::Builder builder(graph()->zone(), 1, 2);
4705 builder.AddReturn(MachineType::AnyTagged());
4706 builder.AddParam(MachineType::Pointer());
4707 builder.AddParam(MachineType::AnyTagged());
4708 Node* try_string_to_index_or_lookup_existing = __ ExternalConstant(
4709 ExternalReference::try_string_to_index_or_lookup_existing());
4710 Node* const isolate_ptr =
4711 __ ExternalConstant(ExternalReference::isolate_address(isolate()));
4712 auto call_descriptor =
4713 Linkage::GetSimplifiedCDescriptor(graph()->zone(), builder.Build());
4714 Node* val_internalized =
4715 __ Call(common()->Call(call_descriptor),
4716 try_string_to_index_or_lookup_existing, isolate_ptr, val);
4717
4718 // Now see if the results match.
4719 __ DeoptimizeIfNot(DeoptimizeReason::kWrongName, FeedbackSource(),
4720 __ TaggedEqual(exp, val_internalized), frame_state);
4721 __ Goto(&if_same);
4722 }
4723
4724 __ Bind(&if_thinstring);
4725 {
4726 // The {val} is a ThinString, let's check the actual value.
4727 Node* val_actual =
4728 __ LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForThinStringActual(), val);
4729 __ DeoptimizeIfNot(DeoptimizeReason::kWrongName, FeedbackSource(),
4730 __ TaggedEqual(exp, val_actual), frame_state);
4731 __ Goto(&if_same);
4732 }
4733 }
4734
4735 __ Bind(&if_same);
4736}

4956Node* EffectControlLinearizer::LowerMaybeGrowFastElements(Node* node,

4959 Node* object = node->InputAt(0);
4960 Node* elements = node->InputAt(1);
4961 Node* index = node->InputAt(2);
4962 Node* elements_length = node->InputAt(3);
4963
4964 auto done = __ MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
4965 auto if_grow = __ MakeDeferredLabel();
4966 auto if_not_grow = __ MakeLabel();
4967
4968 // Check if we need to grow the {elements} backing store.
4969 Node* check = __ Uint32LessThan(index, elements_length);
4970 __ GotoIfNot(check, &if_grow);
4971 __ Goto(&done, elements);
4972

4978 ? Builtins::CallableFor(isolate(), Builtins::kGrowFastDoubleElements)

4986 __ Call(call_descriptor, __ HeapConstant(callable.code()), object,
4987 ChangeInt32ToSmi(index), __ NoContextConstant());
4988
4989 // Ensure that we were able to grow the {elements}.
4990 __ DeoptimizeIf(DeoptimizeReason::kCouldNotGrowElements, params.feedback(),
4991 ObjectIsSmi(new_elements), frame_state);

4994 __ Bind(&done);

4997
4998void EffectControlLinearizer::LowerTransitionElementsKind(Node* node) {
4999 ElementsTransition const transition = ElementsTransitionOf(node->op());
5000 Node* object = node->InputAt(0);
5001
5002 auto if_map_same = __ MakeDeferredLabel();
5003 auto done = __ MakeLabel();
5004
5005 Node* source_map = __ HeapConstant(transition.source());
5006 Node* target_map = __ HeapConstant(transition.target());
5007
5008 // Load the current map of {object}.
5009 Node* object_map = __ LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMap(), object);
5010
5011 // Check if {object_map} is the same as {source_map}.
5012 Node* check = __ TaggedEqual(object_map, source_map);
5013 __ GotoIf(check, &if_map_same);
5014 __ Goto(&done);
5015
5016 __ Bind(&if_map_same);
5017 switch (transition.mode()) {
5018 case ElementsTransition::kFastTransition:
5019 // In-place migration of {object}, just store the {target_map}.
5020 __ StoreField(AccessBuilder::ForMap(), object, target_map);
5021 break;
5022 case ElementsTransition::kSlowTransition: {
5023 // Instance migration, call out to the runtime for {object}.
5024 Operator::Properties properties = Operator::kNoDeopt | Operator::kNoThrow;
5025 Runtime::FunctionId id = Runtime::kTransitionElementsKind;
5026 auto call_descriptor = Linkage::GetRuntimeCallDescriptor(
5027 graph()->zone(), id, 2, properties, CallDescriptor::kNoFlags);
5028 __ Call(call_descriptor, __ CEntryStubConstant(1), object, target_map,
5029 __ ExternalConstant(ExternalReference::Create(id)),
5030 __ Int32Constant(2), __ NoContextConstant());
5031 break;
5032 }
5033 }
5034 __ Goto(&done);
5035
5036 __ Bind(&done);
5037}
5038
5039Node* EffectControlLinearizer::LowerLoadMessage(Node* node) {
5040 Node* offset = node->InputAt(0);
5041 Node* object_pattern =
5042 __ LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForExternalIntPtr(), offset);

5077Node* EffectControlLinearizer::LowerFastApiCall(Node* node) {
5078 FastApiCallNode n(node);
5079 FastApiCallParameters const& params = n.Parameters();
5080 const CFunctionInfo* c_signature = params.signature();
5081 const int c_arg_count = c_signature->ArgumentCount();
5082 CallDescriptor* js_call_descriptor = params.descriptor();
5083 int js_arg_count = static_cast<int>(js_call_descriptor->ParameterCount());
5084 const int value_input_count = node->op()->ValueInputCount();
5085 CHECK_EQ(FastApiCallNode::ArityForArgc(c_arg_count, js_arg_count),do { bool _cmp = ::v8::base::CmpEQImpl< typename ::v8::base
::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(FastApiCallNode::ArityForArgc
(c_arg_count, js_arg_count))>::type, typename ::v8::base::
pass_value_or_ref<decltype(value_input_count)>::type>
((FastApiCallNode::ArityForArgc(c_arg_count, js_arg_count)), (
value_input_count)); do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(_cmp)), 0
))) { V8_Fatal("Check failed: %s.", "FastApiCallNode::ArityForArgc(c_arg_count, js_arg_count)"
" " "==" " " "value_input_count"); } } while (false); } while
(false)
5086 value_input_count)do { bool _cmp = ::v8::base::CmpEQImpl< typename ::v8::base
::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(FastApiCallNode::ArityForArgc
(c_arg_count, js_arg_count))>::type, typename ::v8::base::
pass_value_or_ref<decltype(value_input_count)>::type>
((FastApiCallNode::ArityForArgc(c_arg_count, js_arg_count)), (
value_input_count)); do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(_cmp)), 0
))) { V8_Fatal("Check failed: %s.", "FastApiCallNode::ArityForArgc(c_arg_count, js_arg_count)"
" " "==" " " "value_input_count"); } } while (false); } while
(false);
5087
5088 // Add the { has_error } output parameter.
5089 int kAlign = 4;
5090 int kSize = 4;
5091 Node* has_error = __ StackSlot(kSize, kAlign);
5092 // Generate the store to `has_error`.
5093 __ Store(StoreRepresentation(MachineRepresentation::kWord32, kNoWriteBarrier),
5094 has_error, 0, jsgraph()->ZeroConstant());
5095
5096 MachineSignature::Builder builder(
5097 graph()->zone(), 1, c_arg_count + FastApiCallNode::kHasErrorInputCount);
5098 MachineType return_type = MachineTypeFor(c_signature->ReturnInfo().GetType());
5099 builder.AddReturn(return_type);
5100 for (int i = 0; i < c_arg_count; ++i) {
5101 MachineType machine_type =
5102 MachineTypeFor(c_signature->ArgumentInfo(i).GetType());
5103 builder.AddParam(machine_type);
5104 }
5105 builder.AddParam(MachineType::Pointer()); // has_error
5106
5107 CallDescriptor* call_descriptor = Linkage::GetSimplifiedCDescriptor(
5108 graph()->zone(), builder.Build(), CallDescriptor::kNoFlags);
5109
5110 call_descriptor->SetCFunctionInfo(c_signature);
5111
5112 Node** const inputs = graph()->zone()->NewArray<Node*>(
5113 c_arg_count + FastApiCallNode::kFastCallExtraInputCount);
5114 for (int i = 0; i < c_arg_count + FastApiCallNode::kFastTargetInputCount;
5115 ++i) {
5116 inputs[i] = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, i);
5117 }
5118 inputs[c_arg_count + 1] = has_error;
5119 inputs[c_arg_count + 2] = __ effect();
5120 inputs[c_arg_count + 3] = __ control();
5121
5122 __ Call(call_descriptor,
5123 c_arg_count + FastApiCallNode::kFastCallExtraInputCount, inputs);
5124
5125 // Generate the load from `has_error`.
5126 Node* load = __ Load(MachineType::Int32(), has_error, 0);
5127
5128 TNode<Boolean> cond =
5129 TNode<Boolean>::UncheckedCast(__ Word32Equal(load, __ Int32Constant(0)));
5130 // Hint to true.
5131 auto if_success = __ MakeLabel();
5132 auto if_error = __ MakeDeferredLabel();
5133 auto merge = __ MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
5134 __ Branch(cond, &if_success, &if_error);
5135
5136 // Generate fast call.
5137 __ Bind(&if_success);
5138 Node* then_result = [&]() { return __ UndefinedConstant(); }();
5139 __ Goto(&merge, then_result);
5140
5141 // Generate direct slow call.
5142 __ Bind(&if_error);
5143 Node* else_result = [&]() {
5144 Node** const slow_inputs = graph()->zone()->NewArray<Node*>(
5145 n.SlowCallArgumentCount() +
5146 FastApiCallNode::kEffectAndControlInputCount);
5147
5148 int fast_call_params = c_arg_count + FastApiCallNode::kFastTargetInputCount;
5149 CHECK_EQ(value_input_count - fast_call_params, n.SlowCallArgumentCount())do { bool _cmp = ::v8::base::CmpEQImpl< typename ::v8::base
::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(value_input_count - fast_call_params
)>::type, typename ::v8::base::pass_value_or_ref<decltype
(n.SlowCallArgumentCount())>::type>((value_input_count -
fast_call_params), (n.SlowCallArgumentCount())); do { if ((__builtin_expect
(!!(!(_cmp)), 0))) { V8_Fatal("Check failed: %s.", "value_input_count - fast_call_params"
" " "==" " " "n.SlowCallArgumentCount()"); } } while (false)
; } while (false);
5150 int index = 0;
5151 for (; index < n.SlowCallArgumentCount(); ++index) {
5152 slow_inputs[index] = n.SlowCallArgument(index);
5153 }
5154
5155 slow_inputs[index] = __ effect();
5156 slow_inputs[index + 1] = __ control();
5157 Node* slow_call = __ Call(
5158 params.descriptor(),
5159 index + FastApiCallNode::kEffectAndControlInputCount, slow_inputs);
5160 return slow_call;
5161 }();
5162 __ Goto(&merge, else_result);
5163
5164 __ Bind(&merge);
5165 return merge.PhiAt(0);
5166}

5168Node* EffectControlLinearizer::LowerLoadFieldByIndex(Node* node) {
5169 Node* object = node->InputAt(0);
5170 Node* index = node->InputAt(1);
5171 Node* zero = __ IntPtrConstant(0);
5172 Node* one = __ IntPtrConstant(1);
5173
5174 // Sign-extend the {index} on 64-bit architectures.
5175 if (machine()->Is64()) {
5176 index = __ ChangeInt32ToInt64(index);
5177 }
5178
5179 auto if_double = __ MakeDeferredLabel();
5180 auto done = __ MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
5181
5182 // Check if field is a mutable double field.
5183 __ GotoIfNot(__ IntPtrEqual(__ WordAnd(index, one), zero), &if_double);
5184
5185 // The field is a proper Tagged field on {object}. The {index} is shifted
5186 // to the left by one in the code below.
5187 {
5188 // Check if field is in-object or out-of-object.
5189 auto if_outofobject = __ MakeLabel();
5190 __ GotoIf(__ IntLessThan(index, zero), &if_outofobject);
5191
5192 // The field is located in the {object} itself.
5193 {
5194 Node* offset =
5195 __ IntAdd(__ WordShl(index, __ IntPtrConstant(kTaggedSizeLog2 - 1)),
5196 __ IntPtrConstant(JSObject::kHeaderSize - kHeapObjectTag));
5197 Node* result = __ Load(MachineType::AnyTagged(), object, offset);
5198 __ Goto(&done, result);
5199 }
5200
5201 // The field is located in the properties backing store of {object}.
5202 // The {index} is equal to the negated out of property index plus 1.
5203 __ Bind(&if_outofobject);
5204 {
5205 Node* properties = __ LoadField(
5206 AccessBuilder::ForJSObjectPropertiesOrHashKnownPointer(), object);
5207 Node* offset =
5208 __ IntAdd(__ WordShl(__ IntSub(zero, index),
5209 __ IntPtrConstant(kTaggedSizeLog2 - 1)),
5210 __ IntPtrConstant((FixedArray::kHeaderSize - kTaggedSize) -
5211 kHeapObjectTag));
5212 Node* result = __ Load(MachineType::AnyTagged(), properties, offset);
5213 __ Goto(&done, result);
5214 }
5215 }
5216
5217 // The field is a Double field, either unboxed in the object on 64-bit
5218 // architectures, or a mutable HeapNumber.
5219 __ Bind(&if_double);
5220 {
5221 auto loaded_field = __ MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
5222 auto done_double = __ MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kFloat64);
5223
5224 index = __ WordSar(index, one);
5225
5226 // Check if field is in-object or out-of-object.
5227 auto if_outofobject = __ MakeLabel();
5228 __ GotoIf(__ IntLessThan(index, zero), &if_outofobject);
5229
5230 // The field is located in the {object} itself.
5231 {
5232 Node* offset =
5233 __ IntAdd(__ WordShl(index, __ IntPtrConstant(kTaggedSizeLog2)),
5234 __ IntPtrConstant(JSObject::kHeaderSize - kHeapObjectTag));
5235 if (FLAG_unbox_double_fields) {
5236 Node* result = __ Load(MachineType::Float64(), object, offset);
5237 __ Goto(&done_double, result);
5238 } else {
5239 Node* field = __ Load(MachineType::AnyTagged(), object, offset);
5240 __ Goto(&loaded_field, field);
5241 }
5242 }
5243
5244 __ Bind(&if_outofobject);
5245 {
5246 Node* properties = __ LoadField(
5247 AccessBuilder::ForJSObjectPropertiesOrHashKnownPointer(), object);
5248 Node* offset =
5249 __ IntAdd(__ WordShl(__ IntSub(zero, index),
5250 __ IntPtrConstant(kTaggedSizeLog2)),
5251 __ IntPtrConstant((FixedArray::kHeaderSize - kTaggedSize) -
5252 kHeapObjectTag));
5253 Node* field = __ Load(MachineType::AnyTagged(), properties, offset);
5254 __ Goto(&loaded_field, field);
5255 }
5256
5257 __ Bind(&loaded_field);
5258 {
5259 Node* field = loaded_field.PhiAt(0);
5260 // We may have transitioned in-place away from double, so check that
5261 // this is a HeapNumber -- otherwise the load is fine and we don't need
5262 // to copy anything anyway.
5263 __ GotoIf(ObjectIsSmi(field), &done, field);
5264 Node* field_map = __ LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMap(), field);
5265 __ GotoIfNot(__ TaggedEqual(field_map, __ HeapNumberMapConstant()), &done,
5266 field);
5267
5268 Node* value = __ LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForHeapNumberValue(), field);
5269 __ Goto(&done_double, value);
5270 }
5271
5272 __ Bind(&done_double);
5273 {
5274 Node* result = AllocateHeapNumberWithValue(done_double.PhiAt(0));
5275 __ Goto(&done, result);
5276 }
5277 }
5278
5279 __ Bind(&done);
5280 return done.PhiAt(0);
5281}
5282
5283Node* EffectControlLinearizer::BuildReverseBytes(ExternalArrayType type,
5284 Node* value) {
5285 switch (type) {
5286 case kExternalInt8Array:
5287 case kExternalUint8Array:
5288 case kExternalUint8ClampedArray:
5289 return value;
5290
5291 case kExternalInt16Array: {
5292 Node* result = __ Word32ReverseBytes(value);
5293 result = __ Word32Sar(result, __ Int32Constant(16));
5294 return result;
5295 }
5296
5297 case kExternalUint16Array: {
5298 Node* result = __ Word32ReverseBytes(value);
5299 result = __ Word32Shr(result, __ Int32Constant(16));
5300 return result;
5301 }
5302
5303 case kExternalInt32Array: // Fall through.
5304 case kExternalUint32Array:
5305 return __ Word32ReverseBytes(value);
5306
5307 case kExternalFloat32Array: {
5308 Node* result = __ BitcastFloat32ToInt32(value);
5309 result = __ Word32ReverseBytes(result);
5310 result = __ BitcastInt32ToFloat32(result);
5311 return result;
5312 }
5313
5314 case kExternalFloat64Array: {
5315 if (machine()->Is64()) {
5316 Node* result = __ BitcastFloat64ToInt64(value);
5317 result = __ Word64ReverseBytes(result);
5318 result = __ BitcastInt64ToFloat64(result);
5319 return result;
5320 } else {
5321 Node* lo = __ Word32ReverseBytes(__ Float64ExtractLowWord32(value));
5322 Node* hi = __ Word32ReverseBytes(__ Float64ExtractHighWord32(value));
5323 Node* result = __ Float64Constant(0.0);
5324 result = __ Float64InsertLowWord32(result, hi);
5325 result = __ Float64InsertHighWord32(result, lo);
5326 return result;
5327 }
5328 }
5329
5330 case kExternalBigInt64Array:
5331 case kExternalBigUint64Array:
5332 UNREACHABLE()V8_Fatal("unreachable code");
5333 }
5334}

5336Node* EffectControlLinearizer::LowerLoadDataViewElement(Node* node) {
5337 ExternalArrayType element_type = ExternalArrayTypeOf(node->op());
5338 Node* object = node->InputAt(0);
5339 Node* storage = node->InputAt(1);
5340 Node* index = node->InputAt(2);
5341 Node* is_little_endian = node->InputAt(3);
5342
5343 // We need to keep the {object} (either the JSArrayBuffer or the JSDataView)
5344 // alive so that the GC will not release the JSArrayBuffer (if there's any)
5345 // as long as we are still operating on it.
5346 __ Retain(object);
5347
5348 MachineType const machine_type =
5349 AccessBuilder::ForTypedArrayElement(element_type, true).machine_type;
5350
5351 Node* value = __ LoadUnaligned(machine_type, storage, index);
5352 auto big_endian = __ MakeLabel();
5353 auto done = __ MakeLabel(machine_type.representation());
5354
5355 __ GotoIfNot(is_little_endian, &big_endian);
5356 { // Little-endian load.
5357#if V8_TARGET_LITTLE_ENDIAN1
5358 __ Goto(&done, value);
5359#else
5360 __ Goto(&done, BuildReverseBytes(element_type, value));
5361#endif // V8_TARGET_LITTLE_ENDIAN
5362 }
5363
5364 __ Bind(&big_endian);
5365 { // Big-endian load.
5366#if V8_TARGET_LITTLE_ENDIAN1
5367 __ Goto(&done, BuildReverseBytes(element_type, value));
5368#else
5369 __ Goto(&done, value);
5370#endif // V8_TARGET_LITTLE_ENDIAN
5371 }
5372
5373 // We're done, return {result}.
5374 __ Bind(&done);
5375 return done.PhiAt(0);
5376}

5420// Compute the data pointer, handling the case where the {external} pointer
5421// is the effective data pointer (i.e. the {base} is Smi zero).
5422Node* EffectControlLinearizer::BuildTypedArrayDataPointer(Node* base,
5423 Node* external) {
5424 if (IntPtrMatcher(base).Is(0)) {
5425 return external;
5426 } else {
5427 if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOLfalse) {
5428 base = __ BitcastTaggedToWord(base);
5429 // Zero-extend Tagged_t to UintPtr according to current compression
5430 // scheme so that the addition with |external_pointer| (which already
5431 // contains compensated offset value) will decompress the tagged value.
5432 // See JSTypedArray::ExternalPointerCompensationForOnHeapArray() for
5433 // details.
5434 base = ChangeUint32ToUintPtr(base);
5435 }
5436 return __ UnsafePointerAdd(base, external);
5437 }

5488void EffectControlLinearizer::TransitionElementsTo(Node* node, Node* array,
5489 ElementsKind from,
5490 ElementsKind to) {
5491 DCHECK(IsMoreGeneralElementsKindTransition(from, to))((void) 0);
5492 DCHECK(to == HOLEY_ELEMENTS || to == HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS)((void) 0);
5493
5494 Handle<Map> target(to == HOLEY_ELEMENTS ? FastMapParameterOf(node->op())
5495 : DoubleMapParameterOf(node->op()));
5496 Node* target_map = __ HeapConstant(target);
5497
5498 if (IsSimpleMapChangeTransition(from, to)) {
5499 __ StoreField(AccessBuilder::ForMap(), array, target_map);
5500 } else {
5501 // Instance migration, call out to the runtime for {array}.
5502 Operator::Properties properties = Operator::kNoDeopt | Operator::kNoThrow;
5503 Runtime::FunctionId id = Runtime::kTransitionElementsKind;
5504 auto call_descriptor = Linkage::GetRuntimeCallDescriptor(
5505 graph()->zone(), id, 2, properties, CallDescriptor::kNoFlags);
5506 __ Call(call_descriptor, __ CEntryStubConstant(1), array, target_map,
5507 __ ExternalConstant(ExternalReference::Create(id)),
5508 __ Int32Constant(2), __ NoContextConstant());
5509 }
5510}

5513 Node* kind, ElementsKind reference_kind) {
5514 Node* ref_kind = __ Int32Constant(reference_kind);
5515 Node* ret = __ Int32LessThan(ref_kind, kind);
5516 return ret;
5517}
