5519void EffectControlLinearizer::LowerTransitionAndStoreElement(Node* node) {
5520 Node* array = node->InputAt(0);
5521 Node* index = node->InputAt(1);
5522 Node* value = node->InputAt(2);
5523
5524 // Possibly transition array based on input and store.
5525 //
5526 // -- TRANSITION PHASE -----------------
5527 // kind = ElementsKind(array)
5528 // if value is not smi {
5529 // if kind == HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS {
5530 // if value is heap number {
5531 // Transition array to HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS
5532 // kind = HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS
5533 // } else {
5534 // Transition array to HOLEY_ELEMENTS
5535 // kind = HOLEY_ELEMENTS
5536 // }
5537 // } else if kind == HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS {
5538 // if value is not heap number {
5539 // Transition array to HOLEY_ELEMENTS
5540 // kind = HOLEY_ELEMENTS
5541 // }
5542 // }
5543 // }
5544 //
5545 // -- STORE PHASE ----------------------
5546 // [make sure {kind} is up-to-date]
5547 // if kind == HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS {
5548 // if value is smi {
5549 // float_value = convert smi to float
5550 // Store array[index] = float_value
5551 // } else {
5552 // float_value = value
5553 // Store array[index] = float_value
5554 // }
5555 // } else {
5556 // // kind is HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS or HOLEY_ELEMENTS
5557 // Store array[index] = value
5558 // }
5559 //
5560 Node* map = __ LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMap(), array);
5561 Node* kind;
5562 {
5563 Node* bit_field2 = __ LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMapBitField2(), map);
5564 Node* mask = __ Int32Constant(Map::Bits2::ElementsKindBits::kMask);
5565 Node* andit = __ Word32And(bit_field2, mask);
5566 Node* shift = __ Int32Constant(Map::Bits2::ElementsKindBits::kShift);
5567 kind = __ Word32Shr(andit, shift);
5568 }
5569
5570 auto do_store = __ MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
5571 // We can store a smi anywhere.
5572 __ GotoIf(ObjectIsSmi(value), &do_store, kind);
5573
5574 // {value} is a HeapObject.
5575 auto transition_smi_array = __ MakeDeferredLabel();
5576 auto transition_double_to_fast = __ MakeDeferredLabel();
5577 {
5578 __ GotoIfNot(IsElementsKindGreaterThan(kind, HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS),
5579 &transition_smi_array);
5580 __ GotoIfNot(IsElementsKindGreaterThan(kind, HOLEY_ELEMENTS), &do_store,
5581 kind);
5582
5583 // We have double elements kind. Only a HeapNumber can be stored
5584 // without effecting a transition.
5585 Node* value_map = __ LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMap(), value);
5586 Node* heap_number_map = __ HeapNumberMapConstant();
5587 Node* check = __ TaggedEqual(value_map, heap_number_map);
5588 __ GotoIfNot(check, &transition_double_to_fast);
5589 __ Goto(&do_store, kind);
5590 }
5591
5592 __ Bind(&transition_smi_array); // deferred code.
5593 {
5594 // Transition {array} from HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS to HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS or
5595 // to HOLEY_ELEMENTS.
5596 auto if_value_not_heap_number = __ MakeLabel();
5597 Node* value_map = __ LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMap(), value);
5598 Node* heap_number_map = __ HeapNumberMapConstant();
5599 Node* check = __ TaggedEqual(value_map, heap_number_map);
5600 __ GotoIfNot(check, &if_value_not_heap_number);
5601 {
5602 // {value} is a HeapNumber.
5603 TransitionElementsTo(node, array, HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS,
5604 HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS);
5605 __ Goto(&do_store, __ Int32Constant(HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS));
5606 }
5607 __ Bind(&if_value_not_heap_number);
5608 {
5609 TransitionElementsTo(node, array, HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS, HOLEY_ELEMENTS);
5610 __ Goto(&do_store, __ Int32Constant(HOLEY_ELEMENTS));
5611 }
5612 }
5613
5614 __ Bind(&transition_double_to_fast); // deferred code.
5615 {
5616 TransitionElementsTo(node, array, HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS, HOLEY_ELEMENTS);
5617 __ Goto(&do_store, __ Int32Constant(HOLEY_ELEMENTS));
5618 }
5619
5620 // Make sure kind is up-to-date.
5621 __ Bind(&do_store);
5622 kind = do_store.PhiAt(0);
5623
5624 Node* elements = __ LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSObjectElements(), array);
5625 auto if_kind_is_double = __ MakeLabel();
5626 auto done = __ MakeLabel();
5627 __ GotoIf(IsElementsKindGreaterThan(kind, HOLEY_ELEMENTS),
5628 &if_kind_is_double);
5629 {
5630 // Our ElementsKind is HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS or HOLEY_ELEMENTS.
5631 __ StoreElement(AccessBuilder::ForFixedArrayElement(HOLEY_ELEMENTS),
5632 elements, index, value);
5633 __ Goto(&done);
5634 }
5635 __ Bind(&if_kind_is_double);
5636 {
5637 // Our ElementsKind is HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS.
5638 auto do_double_store = __ MakeLabel();
5639 __ GotoIfNot(ObjectIsSmi(value), &do_double_store);
5640 {
5641 Node* int_value = ChangeSmiToInt32(value);
5642 Node* float_value = __ ChangeInt32ToFloat64(int_value);
5643 __ StoreElement(AccessBuilder::ForFixedDoubleArrayElement(), elements,
5644 index, float_value);
5645 __ Goto(&done);
5646 }
5647 __ Bind(&do_double_store);
5648 {
5649 Node* float_value =
5650 __ LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForHeapNumberValue(), value);
5651 __ StoreElement(AccessBuilder::ForFixedDoubleArrayElement(), elements,
5652 index, __ Float64SilenceNaN(float_value));
5653 __ Goto(&done);
5654 }
5655 }
5656
5657 __ Bind(&done);
5658}

5660void EffectControlLinearizer::LowerTransitionAndStoreNumberElement(Node* node) {
5661 Node* array = node->InputAt(0);
5662 Node* index = node->InputAt(1);
5663 Node* value = node->InputAt(2); // This is a Float64, not tagged.
5664
5665 // Possibly transition array based on input and store.
5666 //
5667 // -- TRANSITION PHASE -----------------
5668 // kind = ElementsKind(array)
5669 // if kind == HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS {
5670 // Transition array to HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS
5671 // } else if kind != HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS {
5672 // This is UNREACHABLE, execute a debug break.
5673 // }
5674 //
5675 // -- STORE PHASE ----------------------
5676 // Store array[index] = value (it's a float)
5677 //
5678 Node* map = __ LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMap(), array);
5679 Node* kind;
5680 {
5681 Node* bit_field2 = __ LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMapBitField2(), map);
5682 Node* mask = __ Int32Constant(Map::Bits2::ElementsKindBits::kMask);
5683 Node* andit = __ Word32And(bit_field2, mask);
5684 Node* shift = __ Int32Constant(Map::Bits2::ElementsKindBits::kShift);
5685 kind = __ Word32Shr(andit, shift);
5686 }
5687
5688 auto do_store = __ MakeLabel();
5689
5690 // {value} is a float64.
5691 auto transition_smi_array = __ MakeDeferredLabel();
5692 {
5693 __ GotoIfNot(IsElementsKindGreaterThan(kind, HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS),
5694 &transition_smi_array);
5695 // We expect that our input array started at HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS, and
5696 // climbs the lattice up to HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS. Force a debug break
5697 // if this assumption is broken. It also would be the case that
5698 // loop peeling can break this assumption.
5699 __ GotoIf(__ Word32Equal(kind, __ Int32Constant(HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS)),
5700 &do_store);
5701 // TODO(turbofan): It would be good to have an "Unreachable()" node type.
5702 __ DebugBreak();
5703 __ Goto(&do_store);
5704 }
5705
5706 __ Bind(&transition_smi_array); // deferred code.
5707 {
5708 // Transition {array} from HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS to HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS.
5709 TransitionElementsTo(node, array, HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS,
5710 HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS);
5711 __ Goto(&do_store);
5712 }
5713
5714 __ Bind(&do_store);
5715
5716 Node* elements = __ LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSObjectElements(), array);
5717 __ StoreElement(AccessBuilder::ForFixedDoubleArrayElement(), elements, index,
5718 __ Float64SilenceNaN(value));
5719}

5894Node* EffectControlLinearizer::LowerConvertReceiver(Node* node) {
5895 ConvertReceiverMode const mode = ConvertReceiverModeOf(node->op());
5896 Node* value = node->InputAt(0);
5897 Node* global_proxy = node->InputAt(1);
5898
5899 switch (mode) {
5900 case ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined: {
5901 return global_proxy;
5902 }
5903 case ConvertReceiverMode::kNotNullOrUndefined: {
5904 auto convert_to_object = __ MakeDeferredLabel();
5905 auto done_convert = __ MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
5906
5907 // Check if {value} is already a JSReceiver.
5908 __ GotoIf(ObjectIsSmi(value), &convert_to_object);
5909 STATIC_ASSERT(LAST_TYPE == LAST_JS_RECEIVER_TYPE)static_assert(LAST_TYPE == LAST_JS_RECEIVER_TYPE, "LAST_TYPE == LAST_JS_RECEIVER_TYPE"
);
5910 Node* value_map = __ LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMap(), value);
5911 Node* value_instance_type =
5912 __ LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMapInstanceType(), value_map);
5913 Node* check = __ Uint32LessThan(
5914 value_instance_type, __ Uint32Constant(FIRST_JS_RECEIVER_TYPE));
5915 __ GotoIf(check, &convert_to_object);
5916 __ Goto(&done_convert, value);
5917
5918 // Wrap the primitive {value} into a JSPrimitiveWrapper.
5919 __ Bind(&convert_to_object);
5920 Operator::Properties properties = Operator::kEliminatable;
5921 Callable callable = Builtins::CallableFor(isolate(), Builtins::kToObject);
5922 CallDescriptor::Flags flags = CallDescriptor::kNoFlags;
5923 auto call_descriptor = Linkage::GetStubCallDescriptor(
5924 graph()->zone(), callable.descriptor(),
5925 callable.descriptor().GetStackParameterCount(), flags, properties);
5926 Node* native_context = __ LoadField(
5927 AccessBuilder::ForJSGlobalProxyNativeContext(), global_proxy);
5928 Node* result = __ Call(call_descriptor, __ HeapConstant(callable.code()),
5929 value, native_context);
5930 __ Goto(&done_convert, result);
5931
5932 __ Bind(&done_convert);
5933 return done_convert.PhiAt(0);
5934 }
5935 case ConvertReceiverMode::kAny: {
5936 auto convert_to_object = __ MakeDeferredLabel();
5937 auto convert_global_proxy = __ MakeDeferredLabel();
5938 auto done_convert = __ MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
5939
5940 // Check if {value} is already a JSReceiver, or null/undefined.
5941 __ GotoIf(ObjectIsSmi(value), &convert_to_object);
5942 STATIC_ASSERT(LAST_TYPE == LAST_JS_RECEIVER_TYPE)static_assert(LAST_TYPE == LAST_JS_RECEIVER_TYPE, "LAST_TYPE == LAST_JS_RECEIVER_TYPE"
);
5943 Node* value_map = __ LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMap(), value);
5944 Node* value_instance_type =
5945 __ LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMapInstanceType(), value_map);
5946 Node* check = __ Uint32LessThan(
5947 value_instance_type, __ Uint32Constant(FIRST_JS_RECEIVER_TYPE));
5948 __ GotoIf(check, &convert_to_object);
5949 __ Goto(&done_convert, value);
5950
5951 // Wrap the primitive {value} into a JSPrimitiveWrapper.
5952 __ Bind(&convert_to_object);
5953 __ GotoIf(__ TaggedEqual(value, __ UndefinedConstant()),
5954 &convert_global_proxy);
5955 __ GotoIf(__ TaggedEqual(value, __ NullConstant()),
5956 &convert_global_proxy);
5957 Operator::Properties properties = Operator::kEliminatable;
5958 Callable callable = Builtins::CallableFor(isolate(), Builtins::kToObject);
5959 CallDescriptor::Flags flags = CallDescriptor::kNoFlags;
5960 auto call_descriptor = Linkage::GetStubCallDescriptor(
5961 graph()->zone(), callable.descriptor(),
5962 callable.descriptor().GetStackParameterCount(), flags, properties);
5963 Node* native_context = __ LoadField(
5964 AccessBuilder::ForJSGlobalProxyNativeContext(), global_proxy);
5965 Node* result = __ Call(call_descriptor, __ HeapConstant(callable.code()),
5966 value, native_context);
5967 __ Goto(&done_convert, result);
5968
5969 // Replace the {value} with the {global_proxy}.
5970 __ Bind(&convert_global_proxy);
5971 __ Goto(&done_convert, global_proxy);
5972
5973 __ Bind(&done_convert);
5974 return done_convert.PhiAt(0);
5975 }
5976 }
5977
5978 UNREACHABLE()V8_Fatal("unreachable code");
5979 return nullptr;
5980}
5981
5982Maybe<Node*> EffectControlLinearizer::LowerFloat64RoundUp(Node* node) {
5983 // Nothing to be done if a fast hardware instruction is available.
5984 if (machine()->Float64RoundUp().IsSupported()) {
5985 return Nothing<Node*>();
5986 }
5987
5988 Node* const input = node->InputAt(0);
5989
5990 // General case for ceil.
5991 //
5992 // if 0.0 < input then
5993 // if 2^52 <= input then
5994 // input
5995 // else
5996 // let temp1 = (2^52 + input) - 2^52 in
5997 // if temp1 < input then
5998 // temp1 + 1
5999 // else
6000 // temp1
6001 // else
6002 // if input == 0 then
6003 // input
6004 // else
6005 // if input <= -2^52 then
6006 // input
6007 // else
6008 // let temp1 = -0 - input in
6009 // let temp2 = (2^52 + temp1) - 2^52 in
6010 // let temp3 = (if temp1 < temp2 then temp2 - 1 else temp2) in
6011 // -0 - temp3
6012
6013 auto if_not_positive = __ MakeDeferredLabel();
6014 auto if_greater_than_two_52 = __ MakeDeferredLabel();
6015 auto if_less_than_minus_two_52 = __ MakeDeferredLabel();
6016 auto if_zero = __ MakeDeferredLabel();
6017 auto done_temp3 = __ MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kFloat64);
6018 auto done = __ MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kFloat64);
6019
6020 Node* const zero = __ Float64Constant(0.0);
6021 Node* const two_52 = __ Float64Constant(4503599627370496.0E0);
6022 Node* const one = __ Float64Constant(1.0);
6023
6024 Node* check0 = __ Float64LessThan(zero, input);
6025 __ GotoIfNot(check0, &if_not_positive);
6026 {
6027 Node* check1 = __ Float64LessThanOrEqual(two_52, input);
6028 __ GotoIf(check1, &if_greater_than_two_52);
6029 {
6030 Node* temp1 = __ Float64Sub(__ Float64Add(two_52, input), two_52);
6031 __ GotoIfNot(__ Float64LessThan(temp1, input), &done, temp1);
6032 __ Goto(&done, __ Float64Add(temp1, one));
6033 }
6034
6035 __ Bind(&if_greater_than_two_52);
6036 __ Goto(&done, input);
6037 }
6038
6039 __ Bind(&if_not_positive);
6040 {
6041 Node* check1 = __ Float64Equal(input, zero);
6042 __ GotoIf(check1, &if_zero);
6043
6044 Node* const minus_two_52 = __ Float64Constant(-4503599627370496.0E0);
6045 Node* check2 = __ Float64LessThanOrEqual(input, minus_two_52);
6046 __ GotoIf(check2, &if_less_than_minus_two_52);
6047
6048 {
6049 Node* const minus_zero = __ Float64Constant(-0.0);
6050 Node* temp1 = __ Float64Sub(minus_zero, input);
6051 Node* temp2 = __ Float64Sub(__ Float64Add(two_52, temp1), two_52);
6052 Node* check3 = __ Float64LessThan(temp1, temp2);
6053 __ GotoIfNot(check3, &done_temp3, temp2);
6054 __ Goto(&done_temp3, __ Float64Sub(temp2, one));
6055
6056 __ Bind(&done_temp3);
6057 Node* temp3 = done_temp3.PhiAt(0);
6058 __ Goto(&done, __ Float64Sub(minus_zero, temp3));
6059 }
6060 __ Bind(&if_less_than_minus_two_52);
6061 __ Goto(&done, input);
6062
6063 __ Bind(&if_zero);
6064 __ Goto(&done, input);
6065 }
6066 __ Bind(&done);
6067 return Just(done.PhiAt(0));
6068}

6070Node* EffectControlLinearizer::BuildFloat64RoundDown(Node* value) {
6071 if (machine()->Float64RoundDown().IsSupported()) {
6072 return __ Float64RoundDown(value);
6073 }
6074
6075 Node* const input = value;
6076
6077 // General case for floor.
6078 //
6079 // if 0.0 < input then
6080 // if 2^52 <= input then
6081 // input
6082 // else
6083 // let temp1 = (2^52 + input) - 2^52 in
6084 // if input < temp1 then
6085 // temp1 - 1
6086 // else
6087 // temp1
6088 // else
6089 // if input == 0 then
6090 // input
6091 // else
6092 // if input <= -2^52 then
6093 // input
6094 // else
6095 // let temp1 = -0 - input in
6096 // let temp2 = (2^52 + temp1) - 2^52 in
6097 // if temp2 < temp1 then
6098 // -1 - temp2
6099 // else
6100 // -0 - temp2
6101
6102 auto if_not_positive = __ MakeDeferredLabel();
6103 auto if_greater_than_two_52 = __ MakeDeferredLabel();
6104 auto if_less_than_minus_two_52 = __ MakeDeferredLabel();
6105 auto if_temp2_lt_temp1 = __ MakeLabel();
6106 auto if_zero = __ MakeDeferredLabel();
6107 auto done = __ MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kFloat64);
6108
6109 Node* const zero = __ Float64Constant(0.0);
6110 Node* const two_52 = __ Float64Constant(4503599627370496.0E0);
6111
6112 Node* check0 = __ Float64LessThan(zero, input);
6113 __ GotoIfNot(check0, &if_not_positive);
6114 {
6115 Node* check1 = __ Float64LessThanOrEqual(two_52, input);
6116 __ GotoIf(check1, &if_greater_than_two_52);
6117 {
6118 Node* const one = __ Float64Constant(1.0);
6119 Node* temp1 = __ Float64Sub(__ Float64Add(two_52, input), two_52);
6120 __ GotoIfNot(__ Float64LessThan(input, temp1), &done, temp1);
6121 __ Goto(&done, __ Float64Sub(temp1, one));
6122 }
6123
6124 __ Bind(&if_greater_than_two_52);
6125 __ Goto(&done, input);
6126 }
6127
6128 __ Bind(&if_not_positive);
6129 {
6130 Node* check1 = __ Float64Equal(input, zero);
6131 __ GotoIf(check1, &if_zero);
6132
6133 Node* const minus_two_52 = __ Float64Constant(-4503599627370496.0E0);
6134 Node* check2 = __ Float64LessThanOrEqual(input, minus_two_52);
6135 __ GotoIf(check2, &if_less_than_minus_two_52);
6136
6137 {
6138 Node* const minus_zero = __ Float64Constant(-0.0);
6139 Node* temp1 = __ Float64Sub(minus_zero, input);
6140 Node* temp2 = __ Float64Sub(__ Float64Add(two_52, temp1), two_52);
6141 Node* check3 = __ Float64LessThan(temp2, temp1);
6142 __ GotoIf(check3, &if_temp2_lt_temp1);
6143 __ Goto(&done, __ Float64Sub(minus_zero, temp2));
6144
6145 __ Bind(&if_temp2_lt_temp1);
6146 __ Goto(&done, __ Float64Sub(__ Float64Constant(-1.0), temp2));
6147 }
6148 __ Bind(&if_less_than_minus_two_52);
6149 __ Goto(&done, input);
6150
6151 __ Bind(&if_zero);
6152 __ Goto(&done, input);
6153 }
6154 __ Bind(&done);
6155 return done.PhiAt(0);
6156}

6158Maybe<Node*> EffectControlLinearizer::LowerFloat64RoundDown(Node* node) {
6159 // Nothing to be done if a fast hardware instruction is available.
6160 if (machine()->Float64RoundDown().IsSupported()) {

6167
6168Maybe<Node*> EffectControlLinearizer::LowerFloat64RoundTiesEven(Node* node) {
6169 // Nothing to be done if a fast hardware instruction is available.
6170 if (machine()->Float64RoundTiesEven().IsSupported()) {
6171 return Nothing<Node*>();
6172 }
6173
6174 Node* const input = node->InputAt(0);
6175
6176 // Generate case for round ties to even:
6177 //
6178 // let value = floor(input) in
6179 // let temp1 = input - value in
6180 // if temp1 < 0.5 then
6181 // value
6182 // else if 0.5 < temp1 then
6183 // value + 1.0
6184 // else
6185 // let temp2 = value % 2.0 in
6186 // if temp2 == 0.0 then
6187 // value
6188 // else
6189 // value + 1.0
6190
6191 auto if_is_half = __ MakeLabel();
6192 auto done = __ MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kFloat64);
6193
6194 Node* value = BuildFloat64RoundDown(input);
6195 Node* temp1 = __ Float64Sub(input, value);
6196
6197 Node* const half = __ Float64Constant(0.5);
6198 Node* check0 = __ Float64LessThan(temp1, half);
6199 __ GotoIf(check0, &done, value);
6200
6201 Node* const one = __ Float64Constant(1.0);
6202 Node* check1 = __ Float64LessThan(half, temp1);
6203 __ GotoIfNot(check1, &if_is_half);
6204 __ Goto(&done, __ Float64Add(value, one));
6205
6206 __ Bind(&if_is_half);
6207 Node* temp2 = __ Float64Mod(value, __ Float64Constant(2.0));
6208 Node* check2 = __ Float64Equal(temp2, __ Float64Constant(0.0));
6209 __ GotoIf(check2, &done, value);
6210 __ Goto(&done, __ Float64Add(value, one));
6211
6212 __ Bind(&done);
6213 return Just(done.PhiAt(0));
6214}

6216Node* EffectControlLinearizer::BuildFloat64RoundTruncate(Node* input) {
6217 if (machine()->Float64RoundTruncate().IsSupported()) {
6218 return __ Float64RoundTruncate(input);
6219 }
6220 // General case for trunc.
6221 //
6222 // if 0.0 < input then
6223 // if 2^52 <= input then
6224 // input
6225 // else
6226 // let temp1 = (2^52 + input) - 2^52 in
6227 // if input < temp1 then
6228 // temp1 - 1
6229 // else
6230 // temp1
6231 // else
6232 // if input == 0 then
6233 // input
6234 // else
6235 // if input <= -2^52 then
6236 // input
6237 // else
6238 // let temp1 = -0 - input in
6239 // let temp2 = (2^52 + temp1) - 2^52 in
6240 // let temp3 = (if temp1 < temp2 then temp2 - 1 else temp2) in
6241 // -0 - temp3
6242 //
6243 // Note: We do not use the Diamond helper class here, because it really hurts
6244 // readability with nested diamonds.
6245
6246 auto if_not_positive = __ MakeDeferredLabel();
6247 auto if_greater_than_two_52 = __ MakeDeferredLabel();
6248 auto if_less_than_minus_two_52 = __ MakeDeferredLabel();
6249 auto if_zero = __ MakeDeferredLabel();
6250 auto done_temp3 = __ MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kFloat64);
6251 auto done = __ MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kFloat64);
6252
6253 Node* const zero = __ Float64Constant(0.0);
6254 Node* const two_52 = __ Float64Constant(4503599627370496.0E0);
6255 Node* const one = __ Float64Constant(1.0);
6256
6257 Node* check0 = __ Float64LessThan(zero, input);
6258 __ GotoIfNot(check0, &if_not_positive);
6259 {
6260 Node* check1 = __ Float64LessThanOrEqual(two_52, input);
6261 __ GotoIf(check1, &if_greater_than_two_52);
6262 {
6263 Node* temp1 = __ Float64Sub(__ Float64Add(two_52, input), two_52);
6264 __ GotoIfNot(__ Float64LessThan(input, temp1), &done, temp1);
6265 __ Goto(&done, __ Float64Sub(temp1, one));
6266 }
6267
6268 __ Bind(&if_greater_than_two_52);
6269 __ Goto(&done, input);
6270 }
6271
6272 __ Bind(&if_not_positive);
6273 {
6274 Node* check1 = __ Float64Equal(input, zero);
6275 __ GotoIf(check1, &if_zero);
6276
6277 Node* const minus_two_52 = __ Float64Constant(-4503599627370496.0E0);
6278 Node* check2 = __ Float64LessThanOrEqual(input, minus_two_52);
6279 __ GotoIf(check2, &if_less_than_minus_two_52);
6280
6281 {
6282 Node* const minus_zero = __ Float64Constant(-0.0);
6283 Node* temp1 = __ Float64Sub(minus_zero, input);
6284 Node* temp2 = __ Float64Sub(__ Float64Add(two_52, temp1), two_52);
6285 Node* check3 = __ Float64LessThan(temp1, temp2);
6286 __ GotoIfNot(check3, &done_temp3, temp2);
6287 __ Goto(&done_temp3, __ Float64Sub(temp2, one));
6288
6289 __ Bind(&done_temp3);
6290 Node* temp3 = done_temp3.PhiAt(0);
6291 __ Goto(&done, __ Float64Sub(minus_zero, temp3));
6292 }
6293 __ Bind(&if_less_than_minus_two_52);
6294 __ Goto(&done, input);
6295
6296 __ Bind(&if_zero);
6297 __ Goto(&done, input);
6298 }
6299 __ Bind(&done);
6300 return done.PhiAt(0);
6301}

6343Node* EffectControlLinearizer::LowerFindOrderedHashMapEntryForInt32Key(
6344 Node* node) {
6345 Node* table = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 0);
6346 Node* key = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 1);
6347
6348 // Compute the integer hash code.
6349 Node* hash = ChangeUint32ToUintPtr(ComputeUnseededHash(key));
6350
6351 Node* number_of_buckets = ChangeSmiToIntPtr(__ LoadField(
6352 AccessBuilder::ForOrderedHashMapOrSetNumberOfBuckets(), table));
6353 hash = __ WordAnd(hash, __ IntSub(number_of_buckets, __ IntPtrConstant(1)));
6354 Node* first_entry = ChangeSmiToIntPtr(__ Load(
6355 MachineType::TaggedSigned(), table,
6356 __ IntAdd(__ WordShl(hash, __ IntPtrConstant(kTaggedSizeLog2)),
6357 __ IntPtrConstant(OrderedHashMap::HashTableStartOffset() -
6358 kHeapObjectTag))));
6359
6360 auto loop = __ MakeLoopLabel(MachineType::PointerRepresentation());
6361 auto done = __ MakeLabel(MachineType::PointerRepresentation());
6362 __ Goto(&loop, first_entry);
6363 __ Bind(&loop);
6364 {
6365 Node* entry = loop.PhiAt(0);
6366 Node* check =
6367 __ IntPtrEqual(entry, __ IntPtrConstant(OrderedHashMap::kNotFound));
6368 __ GotoIf(check, &done, entry);
6369 entry = __ IntAdd(
6370 __ IntMul(entry, __ IntPtrConstant(OrderedHashMap::kEntrySize)),
6371 number_of_buckets);
6372
6373 Node* candidate_key = __ Load(
6374 MachineType::AnyTagged(), table,
6375 __ IntAdd(__ WordShl(entry, __ IntPtrConstant(kTaggedSizeLog2)),
6376 __ IntPtrConstant(OrderedHashMap::HashTableStartOffset() -
6377 kHeapObjectTag)));
6378
6379 auto if_match = __ MakeLabel();
6380 auto if_notmatch = __ MakeLabel();
6381 auto if_notsmi = __ MakeDeferredLabel();

6383 __ Branch(__ Word32Equal(ChangeSmiToInt32(candidate_key), key), &if_match,
6384 &if_notmatch);
6385
6386 __ Bind(&if_notsmi);
6387 __ GotoIfNot(
6388 __ TaggedEqual(__ LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMap(), candidate_key),
6389 __ HeapNumberMapConstant()),
6390 &if_notmatch);
6391 __ Branch(__ Float64Equal(__ LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForHeapNumberValue(),
6392 candidate_key),
6393 __ ChangeInt32ToFloat64(key)),
6394 &if_match, &if_notmatch);
6395
6396 __ Bind(&if_match);
6397 __ Goto(&done, entry);
6398
6399 __ Bind(&if_notmatch);
6400 {
6401 Node* next_entry = ChangeSmiToIntPtr(__ Load(
6402 MachineType::TaggedSigned(), table,
6403 __ IntAdd(
6404 __ WordShl(entry, __ IntPtrConstant(kTaggedSizeLog2)),
6405 __ IntPtrConstant(OrderedHashMap::HashTableStartOffset() +
6406 OrderedHashMap::kChainOffset * kTaggedSize -
6407 kHeapObjectTag))));
